\c 2
\s1 The kingdom of David
\rem /s1 David Anointed King of Judah; David Is Made King of Judah; David Anointed King Over Judah
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 After \add вүҲthat was over\add*, DavidВҰ142217 inquiredВҰ142216 from Yahweh, вҖңShould I go into one of Yehudah'sВҰ142224 citiesВҰ142223?вҖқ
\p вҖң\add Yes,\add*, go,вҖқ Yahweh \add вүҲanswered\add*.
\p вҖңWhere should I go?вҖқ David \add вүҲasked\add* \add again\add*.
\p вҖңTo HebronВҰ142234,вҖқ he said.
\p
\v 2 \add вүҲSoВҰ142236\add* DavidВҰ142238 took his twoВҰ142240 wivesВҰ142241 (AhinoamВҰ142242 the YezreeliteВҰ142243 and AbigailВҰ142244 the \add вүҲwidow\add* of NabalВҰ142246 the CarmeliteВҰ142247) and went thereВҰ142237.\x + \xo 2:2: \xt 1Sam 25:42-43.\x*
\v 3 HeВҰ142254 took his menВҰ142249 who were with him, along with their \add вүҲfamilies\add*, and went to live inВҰ142258 HebronВҰ142259 and the \add surrounding\add* townsВҰ142258.
\v 4 ThenВҰ142261 the Yehudah \add вүҲleaders\add* cameВҰ142261 andВҰ142261 anointedВҰ142264 DavidВҰ142269 as kingВҰ142270 over Yehudah.
\p They told him, вҖңIt was the menВҰ142278 of YabeshВҰ142280-Gilead who buriedВҰ142282 Sha'ulВҰ142285.вҖқ\x + \xo 2:4: \xt 1Sam 31:11-13.\x*
\v 5 \add вүҲSo\add* DavidВҰ142289 sentВҰ142288 messengersВҰ142290 to YabeshВҰ142295-Gilead to tell them, вҖңMay YahwehВҰ142307 blessВҰ142298 you all because you \add вүҲshowed\add* that kindnessВҰ142303 to your masterВҰ142307 Sha'ulВҰ142310 to bury him \add respectfully\add*.
\v 6 Now may YahwehВҰ142317 \add вүҲtreat\add* you all with kindness and faithfulnessВҰ142320, and I myself will also be goodВҰ142325 to you because you did that.
\v 7 \add вүҲMeanwhile\add* now that Sha'ulВҰ142344 your masterВҰ142343 is dead, \add continue\add* to be courageous andВҰ142332 becomeВҰ142336 \add вүҲbrave warriorsВҰ142337\add* as YehudahВҰ142351 has anointedВҰ142348 me as kingВҰ142352 over \add вүҲtheir tribe\add*.
\s1 Disputes between Sha'ul and David's families
\rem /s1 Ishbaal King of Israel; Ishbosheth Is Made King of Israel; Ishbosheth Crowned King of Israel; War Between the Houses of David and Saul
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 8 \add However,\add* AbnerВҰ142356 (Ner'sВҰ142359 son) who'd been Sha'ul's army commanderВҰ142360 had takenВҰ142365 Sha'ul's son Iysh-Boshet\f + \fr 2:8 \ft Also known as Esh-Baal. (See 1 Chronicles 8:33.)\f* across to Mahanayim
\v 9 and \add вүҲdeclared\add* himВҰ142376 to be kingВҰ142376 over GileadВҰ142379, and over the AsheritesВҰ142382 and YezreelВҰ142385, and over EfrayimВҰ142388 and BenyaminВҰ142391, and over all of YisraelВҰ142394.
\v 10 Iysh-Boshet \add вүҲwas fortyВҰ142400 years old\add* when he \add вүҲstarted to rule\add* over the \add вүҲIsraelis\add*, and he \add вүҲruled them\add* for two years.
\p ButВҰ142412 the tribe of YehudahВҰ142417 was loyal to DavidВҰ142420
\v 11 and \add *he\add* \add вүҲruled them\add* for sevenВҰ142434 and a half yearsВҰ142435.
\rem /s1 The Battle of Gibeon; War between Israel and Judah
\p
\v 12 \add One day\add* AbnerВҰ142441 left Mahanayim with \add some of\add* Iysh-Boshet's servantsВҰ142445 and wentВҰ142440 to GibeonВҰ142453,
\v 13 \add вүҲbutВҰ142455\add* YoavВҰ142455 (Tseruyah's son, \add traditionally called вҖҳJoabвҖҷ in English\add*) \add took some of\add* David'sВҰ142460 servantsВҰ142459 and wentВҰ142461 and \add вүҲconfronted\add* them at the GibeonВҰ142466 poolвҖ”one group on each side of the pool.
\v 14 ThenВҰ142480 AbnerВҰ142481 said to Yoav, вҖң\add вүҲLet's get some of these youngВҰ142487 warriorsВҰ142487 to fightВҰ142488 it out in frontВҰ142489 of us\add*.вҖқ
\p вҖң\add вүҲSounds good to me\add*,вҖқ said Yoav.
\p
\v 15 \add вүҲSoВҰ142494 they stood up and countedВҰ142496 off\add* twelve \add вүҲrepresenting\add* BenyaminВҰ142499 and Sha'ul's son Iysh-Boshet and twelve from David'sВҰ142508 servantsВҰ142507.
\v 16 Each of them grabbedВҰ142510 his opponent's headВҰ142513 andВҰ142510 thenВҰ142510 thrust his swordВҰ142515 into his side, so theyВҰ142518 both fell \add down\add* dead togetherВҰ142519. \add вүҲSoВҰ142510\add* thatВҰ142525 placeВҰ142521 inВҰ142513 GibeonВҰ142526 was \add вүҲnamed\add* вҖҳHelkatВҰ142523-HatsurimвҖҷ \add (meaning вҖҳField of DaggersвҖҷ)\add*.
\p
\v 17 \add ThatВҰ142539 led on to\add* a very intense battleВҰ142529 that dayВҰ142534, \add вүҲbutВҰ142528\add* AbnerВҰ142537 andВҰ142528 the IsraeliВҰ142538 menВҰ142538 were \add вүҲdefeatedВҰ142536\add* by David'sВҰ142542 servantsВҰ142541.
\rem /s1 The Death of Asahel
\v 18 Tseruyah's threeВҰ142547 sonsВҰ142548 were thereВҰ142546: YoavВҰ142550, Avishay, andВҰ142544 Asah-El, (Asah-El was a \add вүҲfast runner\add*вҖ”like a wild antelope.)
\v 19 and AsahВҰ142576-ElВҰ142562 chased afterВҰ142563 AbnerВҰ142564 and \add вүҲwouldn't give up\add*.
\v 20 AbnerВҰ142579 turnedВҰ142578 andВҰ142578 said, вҖңIs that you, Asah-ElВҰ142584?вҖқ
\p вҖң\add Yes,\add* it's me,вҖқ he \add вүҲanswered\add*.
\p
\v 21 вҖң\add I'm warning you:\add* \add вүҲStop chasing me andВҰ142588 go afterВҰ142615 someone else instead\add*,вҖқ AbnerВҰ142590 \add вүҲcalled back\add*. ButВҰ142588 Asah-ElВҰ142613 \add вүҲwouldn't give up\add*
\v 22 \add вүҲso\add* AbnerВҰ142619 \add вүҲtried againВҰ142618\add*, вҖң\add вүҲStop chasing me! You'll force me to kill youВҰ142628\add*, thenВҰ142617 how could I faceВҰ142632 your brotherВҰ142636 YoavВҰ142635?вҖқ
\v 23 \add вүҲButВҰ142638\add* \add @Asah-El\add* \add вүҲwouldn't give up so\add* AbnerВҰ142641 thrust the butt end of his spear into his stomachВҰ142646 and it wentВҰ142647 right through and cameВҰ142659 out his back. HeВҰ142667 fell to the ground and died there, and \add вүҲwhen the others caught up, they stopped\add* there.
\p
\v 24 \add вүҲButВҰ142671\add* YoavВҰ142672 andВҰ142671 AbishaiВҰ142673 \add вүҲkept going\add* afterВҰ142674 AbnerВҰ142675. As the sunВҰ142676 was setting, they cameВҰ142679 to the AmmahВҰ142683 hill (east of GiahВҰ142689, along the road to the wildernessВҰ142691 near GibeonВҰ142692)
\v 25 andВҰ142694 the \add вүҲBenyamitesВҰ142697 lined up\add* behindВҰ142698 AbnerВҰ142699 as an \add вүҲcoordinated unit\add* there on top of \add вүҲthe\add* hill.
\v 26 AbnerВҰ142711 calledВҰ142710 out to YoavВҰ142714, вҖң\add вүҲAre we just going to keep killing each other\add*? Don't you knowВҰ142720 that \add вүҲthe only result can be more\add* bitternessВҰ142723? How long will you \add вүҲgo onВҰ142725 before you command your peopleВҰ142732 to stop killing\add* theirВҰ142735 \add вүҲcousins\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 27 вҖң\add вүҲAs GodВҰ142740 lives\add*,вҖқ YoavВҰ142738 \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңif you hadn't \add вүҲsaidВҰ142737 that\add*, thenВҰ142737 surely \add вүҲit would have been morningВҰ142746 before they would have pulled back from the chase\add*.вҖқ
\v 28 \add вүҲSoВҰ142753\add* YoavВҰ142754 had a trumpetВҰ142755 blown and \add &his\add* men \add вүҲstopped fightingВҰ142770 and pursing the IsraelisВҰ142765\add*.
\p
\v 29 ThenВҰ142772 Abner and his menВҰ142773 walked all that nightВҰ142777 through the \add вүҲJordan river plainВҰ142775\add*, thenВҰ142772 crossedВҰ142779 the \add *river\add* and walked all morning until they got \add back\add* to Mahanayim.
\p
\v 30 \add вүҲWhenВҰ142790\add* YoavВҰ142790 had assembled them all \add and counted them, only\add* Asah-ElВҰ142807 and nineteen others had been killed in the battle,
\v 31 \add вүҲalthough\add* \add *they\add* had killed 360 of Abner'sВҰ142816 Benyamite \add вүҲwarriorsВҰ142815\add*.
\v 32 They \add вүҲretrieved Asah-El'sВҰ142827 body\add* and buriedВҰ142828 itВҰ142840 in his father'sВҰ142830 tombВҰ142829 in Beyt-Lehem. ThenВҰ142824 \add *they\add* walked all nightВҰ142837 and got \add back\add* to HebronВҰ142842 \add вүҲatВҰ142829 first\add* lightВҰ142840.
\c 3
\rem /s1 Abner Defects to David
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲNevertheless\add* the war between Sha'ul's and David's \add вүҲfollowers\add* dragged on and on, \add вүҲbutВҰ142844\add* \add overall,\add* David's \add вүҲside had more wins than the followers of Iysh-Boshet\add*.
\s1 David's sons
