\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 2 David'sВҰ142865 \add вүҲwives gave birth to\add* \add six\add* sonsВҰ142866 \add while theyВҰ142862 were based there\add* inВҰ142867 HebronВҰ142867: AhinoamВҰ142871 (the YezreeliteВҰ142872) gave birth to AmnonВҰ142870,
\v 3 thenВҰ142874 AbigailВҰ142876 (the \add вүҲwidow\add* of NabalВҰ142880 the CarmeliteВҰ142881) \add вүҲgave birth to\add* KileabВҰ142875, andВҰ142882 MaakahВҰ142886 (daughterВҰ142887 of KingВҰ142890 TalmaiВҰ142889 of GeshurВҰ142891) \add вүҲgave birth to\add* AbshalomВҰ142883.
\v 4 The fourthВҰ142893 was Adoniyyah (son of HaggitВҰ142897), the fifthВҰ142898 was Shefatyah (son of AbitalВҰ142902),
\v 5 andВҰ142904 the sixthВҰ142904 was Yitre'am (son of David'sВҰ142908 wifeВҰ142907 EglahВҰ142906). \add All six of\add* those \add sons\add* were born to David inВҰ142912 HebronВҰ142912.
\s1 Abner switches over to David
\rem /s1 Abner Joins David; Abner Joins Forces with David; Abner Goes Over to David
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲWhile the war between Sha'ul's son Iysh-Boshet and David'sВҰ142923 supporters continued\add*, AbnerВҰ142924 was strengtheningВҰ142926 himselfВҰ142926 withВҰ142916 Sha'ul's \add вүҲsupporters\add*.
\v 7 \add вүҲNow\add* Sha'ulВҰ142930 had had a slave-wife named Ritspah (daughterВҰ142934 of Ayyah) andВҰ142930 AbnerВҰ142940 slept with her. \add вүҲSoВҰ142930\add* \add Iysh-Boshet\add* \add вүҲdemanded\add*, вҖңWhy have youВҰ142942 slept with my father'sВҰ142946 slave-wife?вҖқ
\v 8 AbnerВҰ142949 \add вүҲbecame very angry atВҰ142981 this challenge from Iysh-Boshet and snapped back\add*, вҖң\add вүҲDo you think I'm Yehudah'sВҰ142962 dog\add* \add hiding out over here\add*? Today I'veВҰ142980 been \add вүҲhelping\add* Sha'ul's \add вүҲfamily\add*: your father, his brothersВҰ142975, and his friendsВҰ142978, and I won'tВҰ142979 let you fall into David'sВҰ142983 \add #hands\add*. \add вүҲYet\add* today you \add вүҲbring some chargeВҰ142984 against me to do withВҰ142981 a\add* womanВҰ142987?
\v 9 May GodВҰ142993 punish \add *me\add* if I don't do for DavidВҰ143002 exactly what YahwehВҰ143001 promised him
\v 10 \add and help with\add* the transferВҰ143010 of the kingdom away from \add *your\add* family and to establishВҰ143014 David'sВҰ143018 \add вүҲkingdom\add* over \add both\add* YehudahВҰ143024 and YisraelВҰ143021, from DanВҰ143025 \add down\add* to BeerВҰ143028-ShebaВҰ143029.вҖқ\x + \xo 3:10: \xt 1Sam 15:28.\x*
\v 11 Iysh-Boshet didn'tВҰ143031 say a wordВҰ143039 back to AbnerВҰ143038 becauseВҰ143040 he was very scaredВҰ143040 of him.
\p
\v 12 Then AbnerВҰ143045 sentВҰ143044 messengersВҰ143046 to DavidВҰ143050 to tell \add <him\add*, вҖңWho should be king of this \add вүҲcountry\add*? \add вүҲLet's come to an agreement and then I could join you\add* \add and help\add* make all of YisraelВҰ143070 turn to you.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 вҖң\add Yes,\add* goodВҰ143073,вҖқ \add @David\add* \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖң\add вүҲI'm happy to comeВҰ143102 to an agreement withВҰ143102 you onВҰ143102 one condition: you mustВҰ143075 bringВҰ143096 myВҰ143106 wifeвҖ”Sha'ul's daughterВҰ143099, MikalвҖ”if you want to be accepted here\add*.вҖқ
\v 14 Then DavidВҰ143110 sentВҰ143109 messengersВҰ143111 to Sha'ul's son Iysh-Boshet saying, вҖңGive \add вүҲMikal back to\add* me. \add вүҲI earnt her as my wifeВҰ143124 withВҰ143131\add* the foreskinsВҰ143132 of one-hundred PhilistinesВҰ143133.вҖқ\x + \xo 3:14: \xt 1Sam 18:27.\x*
\v 15 \add вүҲSoВҰ143135\add* Iysh-Boshet \add вүҲhad her taken\add* from \add &her\add* husbandВҰ143140 (Laish'sВҰ143145 son PaltielВҰ143142),
\v 16 \add вүҲbutВҰ143148\add* he walked along behindВҰ143153 her, weepingВҰ143152, as far as BahurimВҰ143156 \add where finally\add* AbnerВҰ143159 told him to goВҰ143160 \add вүҲback home\add* andВҰ143148 \add вүҲso he did\add*.
\p
\v 17 ThenВҰ143164 AbnerВҰ143166 conferredВҰ143164 with the IsraeliВҰ143170 eldersВҰ143170 saying, вҖң\add вүҲPreviouslyВҰ143171\add* you were wanting DavidВҰ143183 to be king over you,
\v 18 \add вүҲbutВҰ143187 now it's time for action\add*. YahwehВҰ143190 has \add already\add* said, вҖҳ\add вүҲI'mВҰ143198 going to use\add* my servantВҰ143199 DavidВҰ143194 to rescue my peopleВҰ143203 YisraelВҰ143204 from the PhilistinesВҰ143206 andВҰ143187 all theirВҰ143210 \add other\add* enemiesВҰ143210.вҖҷ вҖқ
\v 19 AbnerВҰ143215 also spokeВҰ143212 \add вүҲprivately withВҰ143216 the Benyamites\add*, thenВҰ143212 he wentВҰ143218 to HebronВҰ143225 to tell DavidВҰ143224 \add вүҲprivately what the IsraelisВҰ143233 andВҰ143212 the Benyamites had agreed to\add*.
\p
\v 20 ThenВҰ143240 AbnerВҰ143241 took twentyВҰ143247 men and wentВҰ143240 to David at HebronВҰ143245, and David put on a feastВҰ143256 for \add вүҲall of them\add*.
\v 21 Abner \add вүҲasked\add* David, вҖңMy masterВҰ143269, the king. Let me get \add вүҲready\add* and go, and let me \add вүҲencourage\add* all of YisraelВҰ143275 that they'll \add вүҲmake an agreement\add* withВҰ143280 you so that you will be king over \add вүҲthe entireВҰ143273 area as you've been wanting\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ143258\add* David sent Abner, and he went inВҰ143280 peaceВҰ143291.
\s1 Yoav murders Abner
\rem /s1 Abner Is Killed by Joab; Abner Is Murdered; Joab Murders Abner
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 22 \add Soon afterwards,\add* YoavВҰ143296 and some of David'sВҰ143295 \add вүҲmen\add* arrived after a raid and \add вүҲcarried in\add* a lot of plunderВҰ143299. (AbnerВҰ143303 had already left HebronВҰ143308 because \add David\add* had sentВҰ143310 himВҰ143310 off and he'd left in peaceВҰ143312.)
\v 23 \add вүҲWhenВҰ143314\add* YoavВҰ143314 and all the fighters with him arrived, \add *he\add* was told thatВҰ143318 AbnerВҰ143327 had been there and spoken with the kingВҰ143333, thenВҰ143314 sentВҰ143334 away inВҰ143336 peaceВҰ143336.
\v 24 \add вүҲSoВҰ143338 YoavВҰ143339\add* wentВҰ143348 to the kingВҰ143342 and \add вүҲdemanded\add*, вҖңWhat have you done? AbnerВҰ143349 cameВҰ143348 to you \add вүҲand I can't believe that you'd let himВҰ143354 goВҰ143356, butВҰ143338 he's definitely not here now\add*.
\v 25 \add вүҲSurelyВҰ143364 you realise that\add* \add *he\add* \add only\add* cameВҰ143367 \add вүҲhere to influence you and to find out where you're comingВҰ143374 from and goingВҰ143371 to, and to learnВҰ143368 everything\add* that you're doingВҰ143382?вҖқ
\p
\v 26 \add вүҲOnce YoavВҰ143385 had finished talking to\add* David, heВҰ143398 sentВҰ143388 messengersВҰ143389 \add вүҲto catch up to\add* AbnerВҰ143391. They \add found him\add* at the SirahВҰ143395 cistern andВҰ143384 broughtВҰ143392 him back \add вүҲwithout David'sВҰ143387 knowledge\add*.
\v 27 \add вүҲWhenВҰ143400\add* AbnerВҰ143401 got back to HebronВҰ143402, Yoav tookВҰ143403 him asideВҰ143403 atВҰ143411 the \add city\add* gateВҰ143408 as if to speakВҰ143409 to him privatelyВҰ143411, thenВҰ143400 \add вүҲstabbedВҰ143412\add* him inВҰ143411 the stomachВҰ143414 andВҰ143400 he diedВҰ143415 \add вүҲas vengeance for killing\add* \add @Yoav's\add* brother Asah-ElВҰ143419.
\v 28 \add Later\add* \add вүҲwhen\add* DavidВҰ143423 heard about it, he \add вүҲdeclared\add*, вҖңI andВҰ143422 my kingdomВҰ143429 are innocentВҰ143427 \add вүҲof Abner'sВҰ143436 death in Yahweh's eyes\add*.
\v 29 \add вүҲMay Yoav's extended family continually sufferВҰ143456 from sores or leprosyВҰ143457, and be forced into manual labour or be killed inВҰ143459 battle, or run out of foodВҰ143464 to eat\add*.вҖқ
\v 30 (\add That's how\add* YoavВҰ143466 andВҰ143466 his brother AbishaiВҰ143467 murdered AbnerВҰ143470 because he'd killed theirВҰ143477 brother Asah-ElВҰ143476 inВҰ143478 GibeonВҰ143478 during the war.)
\s1 Abnir's burial
\rem /s1 David Mourns Abner's Death; Abner Is Buried
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 31 Then David \add вүҲinstructed\add* YoavВҰ143486 and all the peopleВҰ143491 with him, вҖңTear yourВҰ143496 clothesВҰ143496 and put on sackclothВҰ143498 and mournВҰ143499 \add вүҲfor\add* AbnerВҰ143501.вҖқ \add Later at the funeral,\add* KingВҰ143502 David walked behind the \add вүҲcoffin\add*
\v 32 and they buriedВҰ143508 AbnerВҰ143511 inВҰ143512 HebronВҰ143512. TheВҰ143523 kingВҰ143515 \add вүҲcried loudly\add* atВҰ143512 the tomb, and the peopleВҰ143527 \add also\add* wept.
\v 33 The kingВҰ143531 \add вүҲsang this song\add* for AbnerВҰ143534:
\q1 вҖңAbner shouldn't have died as if \add вүҲhe was just some drunken fool\add*.
\q1
\v 34 \add вүҲHe wasn't handcuffed or with his feetВҰ143545 in chains\add*.
\q1 \add вүҲHe fell like someone disturbing a burglar.\add*вҖқ
\m And \add so\add* the peopleВҰ143559 wept even more for him.
\p
\v 35 \add вүҲMany peopleВҰ143566 brought foodВҰ143571\add* to DavidВҰ143570 during the dayВҰ143573, butВҰ143563 he promised, вҖң\add вүҲMay GodВҰ143581 severely punish me if I eatВҰ143567 anythingВҰ143597\add* before the sunВҰ143590 goesВҰ143588 down.вҖқ
\v 36 All the people recognised \add David's dignity inВҰ143604 handling this matter andВҰ143599 were pleased with his behaviour, just as they were pleased with everythingВҰ143605 that the kingВҰ143608 did\add*,
\v 37 andВҰ143619 \add вүҲeveryoneВҰ143618 throughout YisraelВҰ143621 knewВҰ143615 that the kingВҰ143627 hadn't ordered for AbnerВҰ143631 (Ner'sВҰ143634 son) to be executed\add*.
\v 38 Then the kingВҰ143638 told his servantsВҰ143641, вҖңDon't youВҰ143643 all \add вүҲrealise that YisraelВҰ143651 lost a leaderВҰ143646 and a greatВҰ143647 manВҰ143647 today\add*?
\v 39 Although I was anointedВҰ143656 as kingВҰ143657, I \add вүҲfeel tender\add* today. Those sonsВҰ143660 of ZeruyahВҰ143661 \add вүҲare more violent\add* than me. May YahwehВҰ143665 repayВҰ143664 \add вүҲevil people appropriately for their actions\add*.вҖқ
\c 4
\s1 The murder of Iysh-Boshet
\rem /s1 Ishbosheth Is Murdered; Ishbaal Assassinated; The Murder of Ishbosheth; Ish-Bosheth Murdered
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲWhen\add* Sha'ul's son \add Iysh-Boshet\add* heard that AbnerВҰ143677 had \add вүҲbeen killed\add* inВҰ143678 HebronВҰ143678, \add вүҲhe lost courage\add* and all YisraelВҰ143683 was horrified.
\v 2 \add *He\add* had two menВҰ143687 who were \add вүҲleaders of raiding parties\add*. They were Rimmon'sВҰ143702 sons BaanahВҰ143697 andВҰ143686 Rekav from BeerotВҰ143709 in the Benyamite region,
\v 3 \add вүҲbutВҰ143715\add* the \add вүҲpeople from BeerotВҰ143716\add* had fled to GittaimВҰ143717 where they've stayed untilВҰ143722 now.
\p
\v 4 (Sha'ul's son Yonatan had a son named Mefiboshet. He was \add вүҲfive yearsВҰ143737 old\add* when the reportВҰ143740 about Sha'ul and Yonatan's \add death\add* came from YezreelВҰ143743. \add @Mefiboshet's\add* \add вүҲnanny\add* pickedВҰ143744 him up \add вүҲto run to safety, butВҰ143727 in her hurry\add* he fell and \add вүҲbecameВҰ143751 crippled in his legs\add*.)\x + \xo 4:4: \xt 2Sam 9:3.\x*
\p
\v 5 \add One day,\add* BaanahВҰ143761 andВҰ143755 Rekav (the sons of RimmonВҰ143758 from Beerot) walked to Iysh-Boshet's houseВҰ143767, \add вүҲarriving in the middle of the day when he was taking a nap\add*.
\v 6-7 They entered the middleВҰ143780 of the houseВҰ143781 \add ?вүҲas if getting wheatВҰ143783\add*, then \add entered\add* the inner room where @Iysh-Boshet was on the bed. They struckВҰ143784 him in the \add вүҲbody\add*, killing him, then they cut off his head. ThenВҰ143776 Rekav and BaanahВҰ143789 took the head and escapedВҰ143791, and walked all night through the Arabah.
\v 8 They took Iysh-Boshet's head to DavidВҰ143829 at HebronВҰ143830 and told the king, вҖңLook, \add here's\add* the head of Ishbosheth, the son of your enemyВҰ143844 Sha'ul who \add вүҲtried to kill you\add*. Today Yahweh's given vengeanceВҰ143854 to my masterВҰ143852 the king against Sha'ul and his \add вүҲdescendants\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 9 Then DavidВҰ143862 answeredВҰ143861 Rekav and his brother BaanahВҰ143869 (the sons of RimmonВҰ143872 from Beerot), вҖң\add вүҲAs YahwehВҰ143878 lives, having\add* delivered my life from every distress,
\v 10 when the \add вүҲmessenger came to TsiklagВҰ143905 thinking he was bringingВҰ143900 me good news and told me that Sha'ulВҰ143896 was dead, IВҰ143907 had him seizedВҰ143902 and executed\add*.\x + \xo 4:10: \xt 2Sam 1:1-16.\x*
\v 11 \add Now\add* how much more when \add вүҲwickedВҰ143916 menВҰ143915\add* have killedВҰ143917 an \add вүҲinnocent\add* manВҰ143920 onВҰ143923 his bed inВҰ143923 his \add own\add* houseВҰ143923. Shouldn't I \add вүҲavenge\add* you \add two\add* \add вүҲfor his murder\add* and removeВҰ143934 you from the earthВҰ143938?вҖқ
\v 12 ThenВҰ143940 DavidВҰ143941 commandedВҰ143940 \add some of\add* the youngВҰ143944 menВҰ143944 and they killedВҰ143945 \add @the two brothers\add* and cut of their hands and feet and hung \add them\add*\f + \fr 4:12 \ft It's ambiguous in the Hebrew whether the hands and feet were strung up, or the actual bodies.\f* beside the Hebron pool, \add вүҲbutВҰ143940\add* they tookВҰ143963 Iysh-Boshet's headВҰ143959 and buriedВҰ143964 it \add there\add* in Hebron in Abner'sВҰ143967 tombВҰ143965.
\c 5
\s1 David becomes king of all Yisrael
\rem /s1 David Becomes King Over Israel; David Becomes King of All Israel; David Becomes King of Israel and Judah; David Anointed King of All Israel
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (1 Chr. 11:1-9; 14:1-7)
\p
\v 1 Then \add the leaders of\add* all of Yisrael'sВҰ143975 tribesВҰ143974 cameВҰ143971 to DavidВҰ143978 at HebronВҰ143979 and saidВҰ143980 to him, вҖңListen, we're \add all\add* \add вүҲclose relations\add*.
\v 2 \add вүҲIn the past\add* when Sha'ulВҰ143994 was \add вүҲour king\add*, you were the \add вүҲone who actually showed leadership of the peopleВҰ144014\add*. YahwehВҰ144008 has \add already\add* told you that you will shepherdВҰ144011 YisraelВҰ144006 and becomeВҰ144019 \add вүҲour king\add*.вҖқ
\v 3 \add вүҲSoВҰ144025 with YahwehВҰ144041 as their witness,\add* all the IsraeliВҰ144028 eldersВҰ144028 made a \add вүҲformal agreement\add* with DavidВҰ144037, andВҰ144025 they anointedВҰ144042 him as king over \add all\add* YisraelВҰ144029.
\v 4 DavidВҰ144056 \add вүҲwas thirtyВҰ144054 years old\add* when he becameВҰ144057 \add their\add* kingВҰ144057 and he reignedВҰ144057 for \add a total of\add* fortyВҰ144058 years:\x + \xo 5:4-5: \xt 1Ki 2:11; 1Ch 3:4; 29:27.\x*
\v 5 sevenВҰ144067 and a half years in Hebron as king of Yehudah, then thirty-three years in YerushalemВҰ144071 as king over all YisraelВҰ144079 and Yehudah.
\s1 David captures Yerushalem
\rem /s1 David Captures Jerusalem; David Conquers Jerusalem; Jerusalem Made Capital of the United Kingdom
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 6 The kingВҰ144083 and his men \add battled\add* againstВҰ144086 the Yebusites who lived \add вүҲin and around\add* YerushalemВҰ144085, \add вүҲbutВҰ144082\add* \add @Yebusites\add* \add вүҲmocked\add* David, вҖңYou'll \add вүҲnever break in hereвҖ”even blindВҰ144102 and crippled men could keep you out\add*,вҖқ because they thought that David couldn't get in.\x + \xo 5:6: \xt Josh 15:63; Jdg 1:21.\x*
\v 7 \add вүҲButВҰ144111\add* David \em did\em* captureВҰ144111 that TsiyyonВҰ144115 strongholdВҰ144114 that \add thenВҰ144111 became known as\add* David'sВҰ144112 cityВҰ144117.
\p
\v 8 He'd told \add <his men\add* that dayВҰ144122, вҖңAnyoneВҰ144126 \add wanting to\add* strike the YebusitesВҰ144127 \add вүҲshouldВҰ144128 use the waterВҰ144129 tunnelВҰ144129 to reachВҰ144128\add* the lame people and the blind peopleвҖ”the ones who are hatedВҰ144136 by David.вҖқ (That's why they say that blind and crippled people shouldn'tВҰ144146 enter the houseВҰ144150.\f + \fr 5:8 \ft Left ambiguous here because it's not clear from the Hebrew. (Some think вҖҳDavid's palaceвҖҷ while others go for вҖҳGod's templeвҖҷ.)\f*)
\p
\v 9 \add вүҲSoВҰ144152\add* David lived inВҰ144154 that strongholdВҰ144154 andВҰ144152 calledВҰ144155 it вҖҳDavid'sВҰ144153 cityВҰ144158вҖҷвҖ”\add вүҲexpanding it onВҰ144154 all sides\add*.
\v 10 DavidВҰ144169 \add вүҲcontinued to grow more powerfulВҰ144171 because\add* YahwehВҰ144172 the commanderВҰ144174 GodВҰ144173 was with him.
\rem /s1 David's achievements
\p
\v 11 KingВҰ144180 HiramВҰ144179 from TyreВҰ144182 sent messengersВҰ144183 to David, then he sent \add вүҲcarpenters and stone-cutters\add* to build a \add вүҲpalace\add* for David.
\p
\v 12 DavidВҰ144200 knewВҰ144199 that YahwehВҰ144204 had establishedВҰ144203 himВҰ144203 as kingВҰ144205 over \add all\add* YisraelВҰ144208 andВҰ144209 that heВҰ144210 \add вүҲwas prospering\add* the kingdomВҰ144211 for the sake of his peopleВҰ144213 the IsraelisВҰ144214.
\p
\v 13 \add вүҲAfterВҰ144230 DavidВҰ144218 moved from HebronВҰ144225 to\add* YerushalemВҰ144222, heВҰ144224 \add вүҲmarried more wives and tookВҰ144217 more slave-wives, all of whom produced more sonsВҰ144231 and daughtersВҰ144232 for him\add*.
\v 14 The namesВҰ144235 of his sons who were born inВҰ144238 YerushalemВҰ144238 were ShammuaВҰ144239, ShobabВҰ144240, Natan \add (NathanВҰ144241)\add*, Shelomoh \add (SolomonВҰ144242)\add*,
\v 15 Ibhar, ElishuaВҰ144245, NefegВҰ144246, YafiaВҰ144247,
\v 16 Elishama, EliadaВҰ144250, andВҰ144249 ElifeletВҰ144251.
\s1 Defeated by David the Philistines
\rem /s1 David Defeats the Philistines; Victory over the Philistines; Philistine Attack Repulsed; David Conquers the Philistines
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (1 Chr. 14:8-17)
\p
\v 17 \add вүҲWhen\add* the PhilistinesВҰ144255 heard that David had been \add вүҲproclaimed\add* as kingВҰ144262 over \add all\add* YisraelВҰ144265, \add вүҲtheir army set off to capture\add* \add *him\add*, \add вүҲbut\add* David heard and \add вүҲretreated\add*\f + \fr 5:17 \ft The Hebrew says вҖҳdescendedвҖҷ, but doesn't tell us either from where (probably Yerushalem) or to where (possibly Masada).\f* to the strongholdВҰ144279.
\v 18 The PhilistinesВҰ144281 \add вүҲmoved inВҰ144284\add* andВҰ144283 took over the Rafa valleyВҰ144284,
\v 19 andВҰ144287 DavidВҰ144288 inquiredВҰ144287 from Yahweh, вҖңShould I \add вүҲattack\add* the PhilistinesВҰ144294? Will you \add вүҲhelp me defeat them\add*?вҖқ
\p вҖң\add Yes,\add* \add вүҲattack them\add*,вҖқ Yahweh \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңbecause I'llВҰ144306 certainlyВҰ144305 \add вүҲhelp you to defeat them\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲSo\add* DavidВҰ144313 \add вүҲattacked\add* and \add вүҲdefeatedВҰ144317\add* them, and saidВҰ144320, вҖңYahwehВҰ144322 brokeВҰ144321 through my enemiesВҰ144325 \add вүҲinВҰ144314 front of me like breaking a dam\add*.вҖқ So he calledВҰ144332 the placeВҰ144335 вҖҳBaalВҰ144337-PeratsimвҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳMaster of breaking throughвҖҷ)\add*.
\v 21 \add @The PhilistinesВҰ144343\add* left theirВҰ144345 idolsВҰ144345 thereВҰ144342, and DavidВҰ144347 and his menВҰ144348 \add вүҲtook them away\add*.
\p
\v 22 Then the PhilistinesВҰ144353 \add вүҲreturned to\add* the Rafa valleyВҰ144356 and took over it againВҰ144352.
\v 23 \add Again\add* DavidВҰ144360 inquiredВҰ144359 from YahwehВҰ144361 who \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖң\add No,\add* \add вүҲdon'tВҰ144363 go straight inВҰ144361. Move\add* aroundВҰ144365 behindВҰ144368 them andВҰ144359 \add вүҲthenВҰ144359 attack\add* them from oppositeВҰ144371 the treesВҰ144372.
\v 24 ThenВҰ144374 when you hearВҰ144375 a sound inВҰ144375 the tops of the treesВҰ144382 \add вүҲthat sounds like marchingВҰ144380, thenВҰ144374 you'll know that YahwehВҰ144388 has gone ahead\add* to strikeВҰ144390 the Philistines' campВҰ144391.вҖқ
\v 25 \add вүҲSoВҰ144394\add* DavidВҰ144395 \add вүҲfollowed Yahweh's instructionsВҰ144398\add* \add #they\add* attacked the PhilistinesВҰ144403 from Geva \add вүҲall the way\add* to GezerВҰ144408.
