\p
\v 1 Then DavidВҰ144413 \add вүҲselected thirtyВҰ144420 thousandВҰ144421 Israeli warriors and gatheredВҰ144411 them together\add*.
\v 2 \add вүҲHe led them to\add* \add Kiriat-Yearim (formerly calledВҰ144441\add* Baalah) in YehudahВҰ144433 to get the boxВҰ144437 of GodВҰ144438 (whose name is YahwehВҰ144444 the armyВҰ144445 commanderВҰ144445) who lives between the two winged creatures on the top of it.\x + \xo 6:2: \xt Exo 25:22.\x*
\v 3 They \add вүҲplaced the sacred chestВҰ144453\add* on a \add вүҲnewly-made\add* cart and started moving itВҰ144459 from Abinadab's houseВҰ144460 whichВҰ144462 was on a hill. UzzahВҰ144464 and Ahyo (Abinadab's sonsВҰ144466) were leadingВҰ144468 the cart.\x + \xo 6:3: \xt 1Sam 7:1-2.\x*
\v 4 They took itВҰ144474 from Abinadab'sВҰ144476 houseВҰ144475 andВҰ144482 Ahyo \add вүҲtook the lead inВҰ144478 frontВҰ144484\add*.
\v 5 DavidВҰ144487 and all the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ144492\add* were celebrating \add вүҲinВҰ144496 God'sВҰ144495 presence\add* with \add вүҲwooden\add* harpsВҰ144500 and lyresВҰ144499, along with tambourinesВҰ144501, shakers, and cymbalsВҰ144503.
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲButВҰ144505\add* when they reached Nakon'sВҰ144515 threshingВҰ144508 floorВҰ144508 the oxen \add вүҲstumbledВҰ144519 so\add* UzzahВҰ144511 reached out \add вүҲto steady the sacred chestВҰ144514\add*.
\v 7 YahwehВҰ144525 \add вүҲbecame furious withВҰ144526\add* UzzahВҰ144526 andВҰ144522 \add вүҲkilled\add* him \add right\add* there by the \add вүҲsacred chestВҰ144536 because he'd touched it\add*.
\v 8 \add Now\add* DavidВҰ144540 \add вүҲgot angry\add* because of Yahweh's outburst againstВҰ144546 Uzzah, andВҰ144547 that placeВҰ144548 has been calledВҰ144547 Perets-Uzzah \add (meaning вҖҳThe punishment of UzzahвҖҷ)\add* untilВҰ144552 today.
\v 9 DavidВҰ144557 was afraidВҰ144556 of Yahweh that dayВҰ144561 andВҰ144563 asked, вҖңHow will Yahweh's boxВҰ144567 \add вүҲget to Yerushalem\add*?вҖқ
\v 10 \add вүҲSoВҰ144570\add* \add *he\add* \add вүҲdecided not to takeВҰ144574\add* Yahweh's boxВҰ144578 \add *there\add* andВҰ144570 \add вүҲredirected\add* it \add instead\add* to the houseВҰ144586 of Obed-EdomВҰ144589 (a GittiteВҰ144590).
\v 11 The \add вүҲsacred chestВҰ144593\add* stayed at Obed-Edom'sВҰ144597 houseВҰ144595 for threeВҰ144599 monthsВҰ144600, and YahwehВҰ144594 blessedВҰ144601 him and all \add вүҲthe household\add*.\x + \xo 6:11: \xt 1Ch 26:4-5.\x*
\p
\v 12 \add вүҲSomeone told\add* KingВҰ144614 David, вҖңYahwehВҰ144618 has blessedВҰ144617 Obed-Edom's \add вүҲhousehold\add* because of the \add вүҲsacred chestВҰ144632,вҖқ so\add* David wentВҰ144634 andВҰ144613 brought God's Box from Obed-Edom's houseВҰ144641 to \add вүҲYerushalem withВҰ144646 much happiness\add*.
\v 13 \add вүҲWhenВҰ144654 the men who were carryingВҰ144651 the sacred chestВҰ144652 had walked\add* sixВҰ144655 stepsВҰ144656, theyВҰ144650 stopped and \add @David\add* sacrificedВҰ144657 a \add вүҲbullВҰ144658 and a fattened calf\add* \add there\add*.
\v 14 ThenВҰ144661 DavidВҰ144661, wearing a linenВҰ144671 \add вүҲapron\add*, danced \add вүҲin frontВҰ144666 of\add* YahwehВҰ144667, \add вүҲputting everything into it\add*.
\v 15 DavidВҰ144673 and all the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ144677\add* brought the \add вүҲsacred chestВҰ144681\add* \add into YerushalemВҰ144682\add* withВҰ144683 shoutingВҰ144683 and trumpet \add вүҲblasts\add*.
\rem /s1 Michal's Contempt for David
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲHowever\add*, as they were entering the cityВҰ144691, \add @David's\add* wife Mikal (Sha'ul's daughterВҰ144694) lookedВҰ144697 out the windowВҰ144700 and sawВҰ144701 KingВҰ144704 David leapingВҰ144706 and dancingВҰ144707 \add вүҲinВҰ144712 frontВҰ144708 of\add* YahwehВҰ144689, and sheВҰ144697 \add вүҲfelt only despiteВҰ144710 for\add* him.
\v 17 They took Yahweh's boxВҰ144717 andВҰ144714 placedВҰ144721 it inВҰ144721 the middleВҰ144722 of the tent thatВҰ144724 David had erected for it. ThenВҰ144714 David \add вүҲoffered burntВҰ144731 sacrifices\add* to Yahweh, as well as peaceВҰ144734 offerings.
\v 18 \add вүҲWhenВҰ144736\add* DavidВҰ144737 \add вүҲhad finished offeringВҰ144738 those sacrifices\add*, he blessedВҰ144741 the peopleВҰ144744 in commanderВҰ144747 Yahweh'sВҰ144746 nameВҰ144745.
\v 19 HeВҰ144756 \add вүҲhanded out a large breadВҰ144763 roll\add*, a cake of \add pressed\add* datesВҰ144765, and a cake of \add pressed\add* raisinsВҰ144767 to each man and womanВҰ144760 \add there\add*, thenВҰ144749 they all returned to their homes.\x + \xo 6:19-20: \xt 1Ch 16:43.\x*
\p
\v 20 ThenВҰ144776 DavidВҰ144777 returnedВҰ144776 to blessВҰ144778 his \add own\add* houseВҰ144781, \add вүҲbutВҰ144776 his wife Mikal cameВҰ144782\add* out to meet him \add вүҲcomplaining, вҖңWhat disgraceful behaviour for Yisrael'sВҰ144795 kingВҰ144794 todayвҖ”dancing when he was wearing so little andВҰ144776 exposing himself to his female servantsВҰ144801 like some brainless person\add*!вҖқ
\p
\v 21 вҖң\add вүҲIt was to thank\add* Yahweh,вҖқ DavidВҰ144808 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ144807\add*, вҖңwho choseВҰ144815 me (rather than yourВҰ144818 fatherВҰ144818 andВҰ144807 any of his family) by appointingВҰ144822 me as leader over Yahweh's peopleВҰ144827 YisraelВҰ144831. I was celebratingВҰ144832 \add вүҲinВҰ144817 frontВҰ144812\add* of Yahweh
\v 22 and I will humiliate and \add вүҲhumble myselfВҰ144836\add* \add even\add* more than that. \add вүҲYet\add* I will \add end up\add* being honouredВҰ144848 by those female servants \add вүҲthat youВҰ144846 were talking about\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 23 \add After that,\add* Sha'ul's daughterВҰ144851 Mikal \add вүҲnever had any more childrenВҰ144858\add*.
\c 7
\s1 Yahweh's promise to David
