\s4 Full kingdom
\r (1 Chr. 17:1-15)
\p
\v 1 Then the kingВҰ144868 \add вүҲmoved into his palace\add*, and YahwehВҰ144870 \add вүҲallowed him to have a time of peace\add* from all his enemiesВҰ144877.
\v 2 \add One day\add* the kingВҰ144880 saidВҰ144879 to the prophetВҰ144884 NatanВҰ144883, вҖңLook, I'm \add here\add* livingВҰ144888 in a houseВҰ144889 \add made\add* of cedarВҰ144890, butВҰ144879 God's boxВҰ144891 is \add вүҲstill there in a tentВҰ144895\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 вҖңGo andВҰ144897 do \add вүҲwhatever you consider best\add*,вҖқ NatanВҰ144898 \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңbecause YahwehВҰ144908 is withВҰ144904 you.вҖқ
\v 4 \add вүҲButВҰ144912 that\add* nightВҰ144913, YahwehВҰ144918 \add вүҲspoke\add* to NatanВҰ144921,
\v 5 вҖңGo and tell my servantВҰ144928 DavidВҰ144931 that YahwehВҰ144934 saysВҰ144933, вҖҳWill you buildВҰ144936 a houseВҰ144939 for me \add вүҲto live in\add*?
\v 6 I haven't lived in a houseВҰ144945 sinceВҰ144946 I broughtВҰ144947 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ144951\add* out of EgyptВҰ144952 \add вүҲright up until now\add*, \add butВҰ144953 rather\add* I was living in a tentВҰ144959 \add вүҲas they moved around\add*.
\v 7 In \add вүҲall those places, I never once queried the leaders to ask\add* why they never builtВҰ144989 a cedarВҰ144992 houseВҰ144991 for me.вҖҷ
\p
\v 8 вҖң\add вүҲButВҰ144994\add* now you should tell my servantВҰ144998 DavidВҰ144999 that commanderВҰ145003 YahwehВҰ145002 saysВҰ145001, вҖҳI myself tookВҰ145005 you out of the \add вүҲgrass field where you looked afterВҰ145009 the sheepВҰ145010 andВҰ144994 goats\add* to become the leader of my peopleВҰ145015 the \add вүҲIsraelis\add*.
\v 9 Everywhere you've gone, I'veВҰ145020 been withВҰ145022 you and \add вүҲdestroyed yourВҰ145031 enemiesВҰ145030 inВҰ145022 front of you\add*, and I will make you \add вүҲfamous like all the famous\add* people onВҰ145022 the earthВҰ145039.
\v 10 I will \add вүҲestablish\add* a place for the \add вүҲIsraelis\add* and put them there to live, and they won't \add вүҲbe afraid because evil peopleВҰ145043\add* won't continue to oppress them \add вүҲlike happened inВҰ145059 the past\add*
\v 11 \add вүҲwhen I appointedВҰ145065 heroes\add* \add (traditionally вҖҳjudgesВҰ145066вҖҷ)\add* over my peopleВҰ145069 YisraelВҰ145070. I will giveВҰ145071 you \add вүҲpeace\add* from all your enemiesВҰ145075, andВҰ145061 I, YahwehВҰ145078, will \add вүҲenable your descendants to rule after you\add*.
\v 12 \add вүҲwhen your timeВҰ145090 on earth comes to an end\add* and you're laid down with your ancestorsВҰ145094, I will appoint one of your sons to be king and I will establishВҰ145103 his kingdomВҰ145106.\x + \xo 7:12: \xt Psa 89:3-4; 132:11; Yhn 7:42; Acts 2:30.\x*
\v 13 He's \add вүҲthe one who'll buildВҰ145109 a temple for me\add*, andВҰ145113 I will \add вүҲmake his descendents reign\add* forever.
\v 14 I myself will become like a fatherВҰ145126 to him, and he'll become like a son to me. When he \add вүҲdisobeys, I'llВҰ145123 punish him like fathers punish their sons\add*.\x + \xo 7:14: \xt Psa 89:26-27; 2Cor 6:18; Heb 1:5.\x*
\v 15 \add вүҲButВҰ145141\add* my kindness won'tВҰ145142 turn away from you like I turned away from Sha'ulВҰ145149вҖ”\add вүҲthe one who I removed ahead of you\add*.
\v 16 Your \add вүҲdescendants\add* andВҰ145154 your kingdomВҰ145156 will remain forever. Your throneВҰ145161 will be establishedВҰ145163 forever.вҖҷ вҖқ\x + \xo 7:16: \xt Psa 89:36-37.\x*
\s1 David's prayer
