\s4 Full kingdom
\r (1 Chr. 18:1-17)
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲSometime later,\add* DavidВҰ145440 \add вүҲattacked\add* the PhilistinesВҰ145443 and \add вүҲdefeatedВҰ145439\add* them, and he \add вүҲcaptured\add* Meteg-Ammah from \add вүҲthem\add*.
\p
\v 2 ThenВҰ145454 he \add вүҲdefeatedВҰ145454\add* the \add вүҲMoabites\add*. \add @David\add* forced them to lie onВҰ145459 the ground and \add вүҲused a length of rope to decide their fateвҖ”those inside twoВҰ145464 lengths of the rope were killed, and those inside the third length were spared\add* and \add so\add* the Moabites becameВҰ145471 David'sВҰ145473 servantsВҰ145474вҖ”bringingВҰ145475 him tributeВҰ145476.
\p
\v 3 ThenВҰ145478 DavidВҰ145479 \add вүҲdefeatedВҰ145478\add* Tsovah's KingВҰ145486 HadadezerВҰ145482 (son of Rehov) \add вүҲwho had tried to reestablish his authority over the Euphrates\add* River.
\v 4 DavidВҰ145497 capturedВҰ145496 1,700 horsemen and twentyВҰ145504 thousand men on footВҰ145507. \add *He\add* hamstrungВҰ145508 all the chariotВҰ145514 \add horsesВҰ145514\add* except for a hundredВҰ145502 of them.
\p
\v 5 ThenВҰ145520 \add вүҲthe ArameansВҰ145529\add* cameВҰ145520 from DamascusВҰ145522 to helpВҰ145523 Tsovah's kingВҰ145525 HadadezerВҰ145524 \add вүҲbutВҰ145520\add* DavidВҰ145528 \add вүҲkilledВҰ145527\add* twenty-two thousandВҰ145533 \add вүҲof them\add*.
\v 6 David \add вүҲstationed\add* garrisonsВҰ145538 in AramВҰ145542 (in DamascusВҰ145540) and \add вүҲthe ArameansВҰ145542\add* becameВҰ145541 David'sВҰ145537 servantsВҰ145544вҖ”bringingВҰ145545 him tributeВҰ145546, and YahwehВҰ145548 \add вүҲhelped\add* David \add win\add* whereverВҰ145553 heВҰ145554 wentВҰ145554.
\v 7 DavidВҰ145557 \add вүҲconfiscated\add* the goldВҰ145560 shieldsВҰ145559 thatВҰ145561 Hadadezer'sВҰ145565 servantsВҰ145564 carried andВҰ145566 broughtВҰ145566 them to YerushalemВҰ145567.
\v 8 \add *He\add* also brought a large amount of bronzeВҰ145576 out of Hadadezer'sВҰ145572 citiesВҰ145571 of Betah andВҰ145570 Berotay.
\p
\v 9 \add вүҲWhen\add* Hamat'sВҰ145584 KingВҰ145583 ToiВҰ145582 heard that DavidВҰ145587 had \add вүҲdefeatedВҰ145586\add* Hadadezer'sВҰ145592 entireВҰ145589 army,
\v 10 \add *he\add* sentВҰ145594 hisВҰ145623 son Yoram to askВҰ145606 for peace \add for Hamat\add* and to \add вүҲcongratulateВҰ145610\add* him for fighting Hadadezer and \add вүҲdefeatingВҰ145615\add* him because Hadadezer \add вүҲoften battled againstВҰ145614\add* ToiВҰ145595. \add @Yoram\add* \add вүҲbrought containers withВҰ145614 him, made\add* of goldВҰ145630, silverВҰ145627, and bronzeВҰ145632.
\v 11 KingВҰ145636 DavidВҰ145639 \add вүҲdedicated\add* them to YahwehВҰ145640, \add along\add* with the silverВҰ145643 andВҰ145644 goldВҰ145644 \add that he'd taken\add* from all the nationsВҰ145649 that \add вүҲthey'd conquered\add*:
\v 12 from Aram and MoabВҰ145654, from the \add вүҲAmmonitesВҰ145656\add* and the PhilistinesВҰ145657, and from Amalak and from the plunderВҰ145659 of Tsovah's KingВҰ145664 HadadezerВҰ145660 (son of Rehov).
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ145667 DavidВҰ145668 made \add more of\add* a nameВҰ145669 \add for himself\add* when he returnedВҰ145670 from \add вүҲdefeatingВҰ145671 eighteenВҰ145678 thousandВҰ145680 ArameansВҰ145674\add* inВҰ145670 the SaltВҰ145677 ValleyВҰ145675.\x + \xo 8:13: \xt Psa 60 header.\x*
\v 14 He \add вүҲstationed\add* garrisons \add вүҲthroughout\add* EdomВҰ145683 and \add made the people\add* his servants, and YahwehВҰ145697 \add вүҲprotected\add* DavidВҰ145695 whereverВҰ145702 \add вүҲthey fought\add*.
\rem /s1 David's Officials; David's Officers
\p
\v 15 \add вүҲSoВҰ145705\add* DavidВҰ145706 \add вүҲreignedВҰ145705\add* over all YisraelВҰ145711 and \add вүҲled all his peopleВҰ145719 with\add* justiceВҰ145715 and \add вүҲintegrity\add*.
\v 16 Tseruyah'sВҰ145724 son YoavВҰ145721 was the army \add вүҲcommander\add* andВҰ145728 Ahilud'sВҰ145731 son YehoshafatВҰ145728 was the secretary.
\v 17 The priestsВҰ145742 were Ahitub'sВҰ145737 son Tsadok and Evyatar's son Ahimelek, and SerayahВҰ145743 was secretaryВҰ145744.
\v 18 Yehoyada's son Benayah \add supervised\add* the KeretitesВҰ145750 and the PeletitesВҰ145751 \add (David's bodyguard)\add*, and David's sonsВҰ145752 were \add his\add* \add вүҲadministrators\add*.
\c 9
\s1 David assists Mefiboshet
\rem /s1 David and Mephibosheth; David's Kindness to Mephibosheth
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲOne day\add* DavidВҰ145759 \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖңIs thereВҰ145761 stillВҰ145763 anyone remaining from Sha'ul's \add вүҲextended family because I'd like to show kindness to them\add* for Yonatan's sake?вҖқ\x + \xo 9:1: \xt 1Sam 20:15-17.\x*
\p
\v 2 \add вүҲNow\add* there was a servant in Sha'ulВҰ145775 householdВҰ145774 named Tsiva and he was summonedВҰ145779 to DavidВҰ145784, and the kingВҰ145786 \add вүҲasked\add* him, вҖңAre you Tsiva?вҖқ
\p вҖң\add Yes, I'm\add* your servant,вҖқ he \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\p
\v 3 вҖңIs thereВҰ145795 \add вүҲanyoneВҰ145797 from Sha'ul's family who's still alive\add*?вҖқ the king \add вүҲasked\add*. вҖң\add If so,\add* I'd \add вүҲlike to show God's kindness to them\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 9:3: \xt 2Sam 4:4.\x*
\p вҖң\add Yes,\add* \add вүҲThere's still one of Yonatan's sons alive\add*,вҖқ Tsiva told the king. вҖң\add вүҲHe's crippled in both legs\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 вҖңWhere is he?вҖқ the king asked.
\p вҖң\add вүҲActually,\add*вҖқ Tsiva told the king, вҖңhe's atВҰ145834 Makir'sВҰ145830 houseВҰ145829вҖ”the son of AmmielВҰ145833 inВҰ145834 Lo-Debar.вҖқ
\v 5 \add вүҲSoВҰ145837\add* KingВҰ145838 DavidВҰ145839 sentВҰ145837 messengers to Lo-Debar to have himВҰ145840 broughtВҰ145840 \add to Yerushalem\add*.
\p
\v 6 ThenВҰ145849 Yonatan's son Mefiboshet cameВҰ145849 to David and fell onto \add вүҲhis knees and bowedВҰ145864 his face down to the ground\add*, and David said, Mefiboshet.вҖқ
\p вҖңI'm your servantВҰ145870,вҖқ he \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\p
\v 7 ThenВҰ145872 DavidВҰ145874 told him, вҖңDon't be afraidВҰ145877, becauseВҰ145883 I'll certainlyВҰ145879 \add вүҲshow you\add* kindness for the sake of your father Yonatan. I'll restoreВҰ145886 all the pastureland that belonged to your grandfather Sha'ulВҰ145893, andВҰ145872 you yourselfВҰ145887 \add вүҲare invited to always eatВҰ145896 atВҰ145883\add* my tableВҰ145900.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 \add @Mefiboshet\add* \add вүҲbowedВҰ145903 low andВҰ145904 asked\add*, вҖңYour servant'sВҰ145906 \add вүҲnothing more than a\add* deadВҰ145912 dog. \add вүҲWhy would youВҰ145908 care about\add* me?вҖқ
\p
\v 9 ThenВҰ145916 the kingВҰ145917 summoned Sha'ul's servantВҰ145921 Tsiva and told him, вҖңI'veВҰ145932 givenВҰ145932 everything that belongedВҰ145927 to Sha'ul and to all his \add вүҲhouseholdВҰ145931\add* to yourВҰ145935 masterВҰ145935.
\v 10 You and your fifteen sons and your twentyВҰ145966 servants mustВҰ145937 work the land for him and \add вүҲharvest the produce to support\add* your master's \add grand\add*son, butВҰ145937 \add *he\add* will eat \add вүҲwith me at my house\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 вҖң\add Yes,\add* myВҰ145989 masterВҰ145977 the king,вҖқ Tsiva \add вүҲrespondedВҰ145969\add*. вҖңYour servant will do everything you've commandedВҰ145976.вҖқ
\p \add SoВҰ145969 from thenВҰ145969 on,\add* Mefiboshet always ate at the king's tableВҰ145989 as if he was one of the king's sons.
\v 12 Mefiboshet had a youngВҰ145997 son named Mika. All \add вүҲTsiva's householdВҰ146002\add* became Mefiboshet's servantsВҰ146005,
\v 13 \add вүҲbutВҰ146008\add* Mefiboshet (who was crippled in bothВҰ146021 legs) lived in YerushalemВҰ146010 because he \add вүҲhad a permanent invitation to eat withВҰ146010 the kingВҰ146015\add*.
\c 10
\s1 Yisrael defeats the Ammonites and the Arameans
\rem /s1 David Defeats the Ammonites and the Syrians; David Defeats the Ammonites; The Ammonites and Arameans Are Defeated
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (1 Chr. 19:1-19)
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲSome time later,\add* the \add вүҲAmmonite\add* king died, and hisВҰ146036 son HanunВҰ146034 replace him as king.
\v 2 вҖңI'llВҰ146040 be kind to Nahash'sВҰ146049 son Hanun,вҖқ DavidВҰ146039 said, вҖңjust like his father was kind to me.вҖқ SoВҰ146038 \add *he\add* sent servants \add to Hanun\add* \add вүҲto convey his condolences\add*.
\p \add вүҲWhenВҰ146038\add* \add *they\add* \add вүҲarrived inВҰ146058 the AmmonВҰ146069 regionВҰ146067\add*,
\v 3 the \add вүҲAmmonite commanders\add* saidВҰ146071 to theirВҰ146079 masterВҰ146079 HanunВҰ146078, вҖң\add вүҲDo you think that DavidВҰ146081 really sent condolences to honourВҰ146080 yourВҰ146085 late father\add*? Isn't it \add more likely\add* \add вүҲbecause he wanted them to spy onВҰ146085 us, andВҰ146071 to exploreВҰ146093 the cityВҰ146096 so he could more easily conquer it\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ146106\add* HanunВҰ146107 \add вүҲseized\add* David'sВҰ146111 servantsВҰ146110 and had half of their beardsВҰ146116 shavedВҰ146112 off and their robesВҰ146120 cut inВҰ146121 half \add all the way\add* up to their buttocksВҰ146123, thenВҰ146106 he sentВҰ146124 them off.
\v 5 They \add вүҲsentВҰ146128 messengers ahead\add* to tell DavidВҰ146127 because theyВҰ146132 were very humiliatedВҰ146134, andВҰ146126 the kingВҰ146137 told them to stay inВҰ146139 Yeriho before returningВҰ146144 when their beardsВҰ146143 grew back.
\p
\v 6 ThenВҰ146146 the \add вүҲAmmonite leaders realisedВҰ146146 that they'd now caused DavidВҰ146151 to despise them, so\add* they hiredВҰ146156 twentyВҰ146167 thousand \add вүҲAramean\add* \add (or Syrian)\add* \add вүҲmercenaries\add* from Beyt-RehobВҰ146162 and Tsovah, and \add another\add* one thousand from Maakah and twelve thousand from Tov.
\v 7 \add вүҲWhenВҰ146184\add* DavidВҰ146185 heard \add <that\add*, he sentВҰ146186 YoavВҰ146189 in with the entireВҰ146191 army.
\v 8 The \add вүҲAmmonitesВҰ146198\add* came out the \add city\add* gateВҰ146202 andВҰ146196 \add вүҲorganised themselvesВҰ146210 for battleВҰ146200 atВҰ146211 the entranceВҰ146201\add*, while \add вүҲtheir hired mercenaries stood apart out inВҰ146211 the countrysideВҰ146211\add*.
\p
\v 9 \add вүҲWhenВҰ146213 YoavВҰ146214 sawВҰ146213 that he was disadvantaged withВҰ146226 enemy lines both inВҰ146226 frontВҰ146221\add* and behindВҰ146222, he \add вүҲselected certain Israeli warriors\add* and placed them to battleВҰ146220 the \add вүҲAramean mercenaries\add*,
\v 10 leaving the others to face the AmmonitesВҰ146242 under the commandВҰ146236 of his brother AvishayВҰ146237,
\v 11 telling him, вҖңIf \add вүҲthe ArameansВҰ146248\add* are too strong for me, then you come \add вүҲand rescue us, butВҰ146244\add* if the \add вүҲAmmonitesВҰ146256\add* are too strong for you, then I'llВҰ146259 \add вүҲcome and rescue\add* you.
\v 12 Be strongВҰ146263 and courageousВҰ146264 for \add the sake of\add* our peopleВҰ146267 and our god's citiesВҰ146269, and YahwehВҰ146271 will do \add вүҲwhatever he considers right\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 \add вүҲSoВҰ146276\add* YoavВҰ146277 andВҰ146276 \add вүҲhisВҰ146284 men advanced to attack the ArameanВҰ146282 mercenaries butВҰ146276 theyВҰ146283 fled away from them\add*.
\v 14 \add вүҲWhenВҰ146286 the Ammonites sawВҰ146288 the ArameansВҰ146292 running away, they started retreating from AbishaiВҰ146295 and wentВҰ146296 back into\add* the cityВҰ146297, \add вүҲso\add* YoavВҰ146299 \add вүҲwithdrew from attacking the Ammonites and returnedВҰ146298\add* to YerushalemВҰ146304.
\p
\v 15 \add вүҲWhenВҰ146306 the ArameansВҰ146307 realisedВҰ146306 that they'd been defeatedВҰ146309 by\add* YisraelВҰ146311, they assembled \add all their warriors\add* togetherВҰ146313 \add again\add*.
\v 16 \add King\add* Hadadezer \add (from Tsovah)\add* \add вүҲcalled for Aramean warriors\add* from beyondВҰ146322 the \add Euphrates\add* River andВҰ146315 theyВҰ146324 cameВҰ146324 to Heylam. Shovak was Hadadezer'sВҰ146316 army commanderВҰ146327.
\v 17 \add вүҲWhenВҰ146333\add* David \add вүҲheard that\add*, he assembled all \add вүҲthe IsraeliВҰ146339 warriors\add* and they crossed the YordanВҰ146345 \add вүҲgoing towards\add* HelamВҰ146347. \add вүҲThe ArameansВҰ146349 cameВҰ146346 out\add* to meet David and \add вүҲthe two sides foughtВҰ146352 each other\add*.
\v 18 \add вүҲButВҰ146355\add* \add again\add* \add вүҲthe ArameansВҰ146356\add* fled from \add вүҲthe IsraelisВҰ146357\add*, and DavidВҰ146360 killedВҰ146359 sevenВҰ146362 hundredВҰ146363 \add вүҲAramean charioteersВҰ146364\add* and fortyВҰ146365 thousandВҰ146366 cavalry, and theirВҰ146372 commanderВҰ146370 Shobak was struckВҰ146373 and diedВҰ146374 thereВҰ146375 \add also\add*.
\v 19 ThenВҰ146377 all the kingsВҰ146380 \add вүҲassociated with HadadezerВҰ146382 realisedВҰ146377 they couldn't defeatВҰ146384\add* YisraelВҰ146386, \add вүҲso\add* they made peaceВҰ146387 with \add вүҲthe IsraelisВҰ146390\add* and servedВҰ146391 them, and \add so\add* the ArameansВҰ146393 were afraid to \add try to\add* rescue the \add вүҲAmmonitesВҰ146399\add* againВҰ146395.
\c 11
\s1 David takes Uriyyah's wife
\rem /s1 David and Bathsheba; David Commits Adultery with Bathsheba; David's crimes
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲThe next springВҰ146403 (when kingsВҰ146408 usually goВҰ146407 to war)\add*, DavidВҰ146411 sentВҰ146410 YoavВҰ146414 and his \add вүҲofficials\add* and all the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ146421 warriors\add*, and they \add вүҲdefeated the AmmonitesВҰ146428 and besiegedВҰ146429\add* RabbahВҰ146432.\x + \xo 11:1: \xt 1Ch 20:1.\x*
\p \add вүҲButВҰ146402\add* David stayed inВҰ146435 YerushalemВҰ146435,
\v 2 and \add вүҲearly one\add* eveningВҰ146441 \add *he\add* got up from \add вүҲa nap\add* and walkedВҰ146446 around the \add вүҲpalace roof area\add*. FromВҰ146443 \add вүҲthere\add* he saw a woman bathingВҰ146455, and she was very \add вүҲgood-looking\add*.
\v 3 DavidВҰ146464 sent \add a messenger\add* \add вүҲto find out who she was, andВҰ146463 was told\add*, вҖңThat's Eliam'sВҰ146476 daughterВҰ146474 BatshevaвҖ”Uriyyah the Hittite'sВҰ146479 wife.вҖқ
\v 4 Then \add *he\add* sentВҰ146481 messengersВҰ146483 \add вүҲto get\add* her, and she cameВҰ146485 and he sleptВҰ146487 with her. (She had been \add вүҲpurifyingВҰ146491 herselfВҰ146491 after the completion of her menstrual period\add*.) Then she returnedВҰ146493 to her houseВҰ146496.
\p
\v 5 \add вүҲAfterВҰ146505 some time,\add* the womanВҰ146499 \add realised that she\add* was pregnant, andВҰ146498 \add so\add* she informed DavidВҰ146502.
\v 6 David sent to Yoav, вҖңSend Uriyyah the HittiteВҰ146517 \add here\add* to me.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ146507\add* Yoav sent Uriyyah to David.
\v 7 \add вүҲWhenВҰ146528 he arrived, DavidВҰ146531 askedВҰ146530 him about how YoavВҰ146533 and his men were doing, and how the battleВҰ146537 was going\add*,
\v 8 thenВҰ146539 \add *he\add* told \add *him\add*, вҖңGo to your house and \add вүҲrelax\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ146539\add* Uriyyah \add вүҲleft the palace\add* and the king \add вүҲsent a gift to be delivered to his house\add*.
\v 9 \add вүҲButВҰ146556\add* UriyyahВҰ146557 didn'tВҰ146566 go homeвҖ”\add вүҲinstead he sleptВҰ146556 at the palace entranceВҰ146558\add* with all the king's servantsВҰ146564,
\v 10 \add The next day,\add* DavidВҰ146573 was informed that Uriyyah didn't go home to his house, \add вүҲso\add* \add *he\add* \add вүҲasked\add* \add *him\add*, вҖң\add вүҲDidn't you just get back from a long journeyВҰ146588\add*? Why didn't you go \add вүҲhome\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 11 вҖңThe \add вүҲsacred chestВҰ146604\add* and \add the warriors from\add* YisraelВҰ146605 and Yehudah are livingВҰ146607 in tents,вҖқ Uriyyah \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖңAnd my master, YoavВҰ146610, and my master's servantsВҰ146611 are camping \add вүҲout in the open\add*. \add вүҲSoВҰ146599 I couldn't just\add* go to my houseВҰ146622 to eat and to drinkВҰ146624 and to sleep withВҰ146608 my wife. By your life and by the life of your spirit, I \add вүҲcouldn't do that\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 вҖң\add Well,\add* stay here today also,вҖқ DavidВҰ146641 told \add *him\add*, вҖңand tomorrowВҰ146650 I'llВҰ146651 send you \add back\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ146640\add* Uriyyah stayed inВҰ146646 YerushalemВҰ146654 that day and the following day,
\v 13 and David \add вүҲsummoned\add* him \add over\add*, and they ateВҰ146663 and drankВҰ146665 together, and \add @David\add* got him drunkВҰ146666. \add вүҲButВҰ146659 even thenВҰ146659\add*, \add @Uriyyah\add* didn'tВҰ146678 go back to his houseВҰ146677, butВҰ146659 when he left in the eveningВҰ146668 he went \add back\add* to sleep \add in the dorm\add* withВҰ146668 his master'sВҰ146674 servantsВҰ146673.
\rem /s1 David Arranges for Uriah's Death; David Has Uriah Killed
\p
\v 14 \add вүҲThe next morningВҰ146682\add*, DavidВҰ146684 wroteВҰ146683 a \add вүҲnote\add* to YoavВҰ146688 andВҰ146681 \add told\add* Uriyyah \add вүҲto deliver it\add*.
\v 15 He'd written, вҖң\add вүҲPlace\add* Uriyyah inВҰ146694 the frontВҰ146702 \add вүҲwhere the fightingВҰ146704 is\add* strongest, thenВҰ146693 \add вүҲfall\add* back from behindВҰ146707 himВҰ146707 so that he'll be struckВҰ146708 andВҰ146693 dieВҰ146709.вҖқ
\v 16 \add вүҲSo\add* as YoavВҰ146714 \add вүҲwas surrounding\add* the cityВҰ146717, he \add вүҲplacedВҰ146724\add* Uriyyah whereВҰ146725 he knewВҰ146726 \add вүҲthe strongest enemy warriorsВҰ146728\add* \add would be fighting\add*.
\v 17 The \add вүҲwarriorsВҰ146734\add* from the cityВҰ146735 came out and foughtВҰ146736 against Yoav's \add вүҲmenВҰ146734\add*, and some of David'sВҰ146745 servantsВҰ146744 \add вүҲwere killed\add* and \add вүҲso was\add* Uriyyah.
\p
\v 18 ThenВҰ146751 YoavВҰ146752 sentВҰ146751 \add a messenger\add* to DavidВҰ146754 \add вүҲto give him a full account of the battleВҰ146760\add*.
\v 19 He toldВҰ146762 the messengerВҰ146765, вҖң\add вүҲOnce you've finishedВҰ146767 tellingВҰ146773 all the details of the battleВҰ146772\add* to the kingВҰ146776,
\v 20 if \add *he\add* gets angry andВҰ146784 \add вүҲasks\add*, вҖҳWhy did you all \add вүҲgo so close in\add* to the cityВҰ146790 to fightВҰ146791? Didn't you knowВҰ146793 that they'd shootВҰ146797 \add down\add* from the wallВҰ146799?
\v 21 \add вүҲWasn't Yerub-Beshet's son Abimilek killed by a womanВҰ146812 inВҰ146820 Tevets\add* when sheВҰ146813 threw a millstone down from the wall? Why did you approach the wall?вҖҷ Then you should sayВҰ146826, вҖҳYour servantВҰ146828 Uriyyah the HittiteВҰ146830 is also dead.вҖҷ вҖқ\x + \xo 11:21: \xt Jdg 9:53.\x*
\p
\v 22 \add вүҲSoВҰ146833\add* the messengerВҰ146834 left and wentВҰ146833 and told DavidВҰ146837 everything that YoavВҰ146843 had told himВҰ146842,
\v 23 saying, вҖң\add вүҲTheirВҰ146849 menВҰ146854 gained ground andВҰ146845 came out againstВҰ146856 us in the countrysideВҰ146857, butВҰ146845 weВҰ146858 forced them back to their city\add* gateВҰ146863.
\v 24 ThenВҰ146865 \add &their\add* archersВҰ146867 were shooting at your men from \add the top of\add* the wallВҰ146873 andВҰ146865 \add вүҲsome of your men were killed, includingВҰ146874\add* your servantВҰ146878 UriyyahВҰ146879 the HittiteВҰ146880.вҖқ
\p
\v 25 DavidВҰ146885 \add вүҲsent the messengerВҰ146888 back to encourageВҰ146915 YoavВҰ146894\add*, вҖңDon't let \add вүҲyourself be upset by what happened\add* because \add вүҲno one knows who might die inВҰ146898 a battle\add*. \add вүҲReinforce yourВҰ146898 battle\add* againstВҰ146911 the cityВҰ146913 and tear it down.вҖқ
\p
\v 26 \add вүҲWhenВҰ146917 Uriyyah's wifeВҰ146918 Batsheva heardВҰ146917 that herВҰ146928 husbandВҰ146928 had been killed\add*, she mournedВҰ146925 for \add *him\add*.
\v 27 \add вүҲWhenВҰ146930 her timeВҰ146931 of mourningВҰ146931 was over\add*, David sentВҰ146932 for her and broughtВҰ146934 her to \add вүҲthe palace\add*. She becameВҰ146938 a wife to him and bore a son for him, \add вүҲbutВҰ146930 YahwehВҰ146952 was unhappy about what\add* David had done.
\c 12
\s1 Natan brings rebuke to David
\rem /s1 Nathan Rebukes David; Nathan's Message and David's Repentance
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲSo\add* YahwehВҰ146956 sentВҰ146955 NatanВҰ146959 to DavidВҰ146962 \add вүҲto tell\add* him, вҖң\add Once\add* \add вүҲthere was a rich man and a poor man living inВҰ146970 the same cityВҰ146970\add*.\x + \xo 12:1: \xt Psa 51 header.\x*
\v 2 The rich manВҰ146977 \add вүҲhad a large number\add* of flocksВҰ146979 andВҰ146980 herdsВҰ146980,
\v 3 \add вүҲbutВҰ146984\add* the poor manВҰ146984 only had one little female lamb thatВҰ146994 he'd bought. It grew up withВҰ147007 him and his sons, and would eat his left-overs and drink from his cup and lay down inВҰ147007 his lapвҖ”it was like a daughterВҰ147012 to him.
\v 4 \add OneВҰ147028 day\add* the rich man \add вүҲhad a visitorВҰ147015, butВҰ147014 instead of taking one of his own animals for a meal, he killed the poor man's lamb andВҰ147014 preparedВҰ147033 it for the meal for his guest\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 DavidВҰ147041 \add вүҲgot very angry listening to that\add* andВҰ147038 told NatanВҰ147047, вҖңBy the lifeВҰ147048 of YahwehВҰ147050, the man that did that \add вүҲdefinitely deserves to be put to\add* deathВҰ147054!
\v 6 He mustВҰ147062 \add вүҲpay back four lambs\add* for doing that andВҰ147071 for \add вүҲhaving no pity\add* \add on that poor man\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 ThenВҰ147077 NatanВҰ147078 saidВҰ147077 to DavidВҰ147081, вҖңYou are \add that rich\add* manВҰ147083. YahwehВҰ147087, the godВҰ147088 of Yisrael, saysВҰ147086 to you: вҖҳI myself anointedВҰ147091 you as kingВҰ147092 over Yisrael, andВҰ147077 I myself \add вүҲkept you safe from\add* Sha'ulВҰ147099.
\v 8 I gave you the house that belonged to your master, \add вүҲas well as\add* his wivesВҰ147109. I \add вүҲmade you king over\add* \add both\add* YisraelВҰ147117 and Yehudah. And \add вүҲif that wasn't enough, I've given you more and more\add*.
\v 9 \add вүҲSo\add* why have you despisedВҰ147128 \add вүҲmy commands\add* by doingВҰ147134 \add вүҲwhat you knew was evil\add*? You had Uriyyah the HittiteВҰ147140 killedВҰ147150 withВҰ147136 \add вүҲan Ammonite sword\add* and you took his wife for yourselfВҰ147147.
\v 10 \add вүҲSoВҰ147155\add* now, because you despisedВҰ147166 me and tookВҰ147167 Uriyyah'sВҰ147172 wifeВҰ147170 as your own, \add вүҲwar and violence will never go away from you and your descendants\add*.
\v 11 \add вүҲI will cause a disaster to hit you from within your own householdВҰ147186вҖ”I'llВҰ147187 take your wives and give them to a family member right in front of your eyesВҰ147191, and he will let everyone know that he's sleeping\add* with your wives.\x + \xo 12:11-12: \xt 2Sam 16:22.\x*
\v 12 \add вүҲYou did what you did\add* in secretВҰ147205, \add вүҲbutВҰ147206\add* I myself will do all this \add вүҲin public\add* before all YisraelВҰ147215.вҖҷвҖқ
\rem /s1 David Confesses His Guilt
\p
\v 13 вҖң\add Yes,\add* I'veВҰ147225 sinnedВҰ147225 against Yahweh,вҖқ DavidВҰ147221 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ147220\add* to NatanВҰ147224.
\p вҖңYahweh has takenВҰ147236 away yourВҰ147237 sinВҰ147237,вҖқ Natan \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖңYou won'tВҰ147238 dieВҰ147239.
\v 14 NeverthelessВҰ147241, because you have utterly disrespected YahwehВҰ147249 inВҰ147250 this matter, also your \add вүҲnew\add* son is certainly going to die.вҖқ
\v 15 Then NatanВҰ147260 wentВҰ147259 home.
\s1 David's son dies
\rem /s1 David's Son Dies; Bathsheba's Child Dies
\s4 Full kingdom
\p Then YahwehВҰ147265 \add вүҲcaused the baby (that Uriyyah's wifeВҰ147271 had given birth to) to\add* get sickВҰ147275.
\v 16 DavidВҰ147278 \add вүҲpleaded with\add* YahwehВҰ147285 for the boy's sake, and he fastedВҰ147284, and he spent the \add entireВҰ147288\add* nightВҰ147288 lying down on the groundВҰ147290.
\v 17 The \add вүҲinfluential members\add* of his householdВҰ147294 got beside him to try to get him up from the ground, butВҰ147292 he \add вүҲwouldn't budge\add*, andВҰ147292 he wouldn't eat \add вүҲanything they brought\add*.
\v 18 ThenВҰ147308 onВҰ147326 the seventhВҰ147310 day, the baby died, \add вүҲbutВҰ147308\add* David'sВҰ147315 servantsВҰ147314 were afraid to tell him because \add вүҲafter seeing his response when the child was sick, they were afraid of what he might do to himself when he found out that his son\add* had died.
\p
\v 19 \add вүҲHowever, when\add* DavidВҰ147344 noticedВҰ147343 his servants whisperingВҰ147347 together, he \add вүҲrealisedВҰ147343 that the baby must have died, andВҰ147343 he asked\add* \add *them\add*, вҖңDid the baby die?вҖқ
\p вҖң\add Yes,\add*вҖқ they \add вүҲanswered\add*, вҖңhe \add вүҲpassed away\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 Then DavidВҰ147364 got up from the groundВҰ147365 and washedВҰ147366, and he \add вүҲrubbed lotions on\add* and changedВҰ147368 his clothesВҰ147369, thenВҰ147363 he entered Yahweh's \add вүҲtent and worshippedВҰ147375 him\add*. Then he \add вүҲwent back home and askedВҰ147380 for food to be servedВҰ147381\add*, and he ateВҰ147384.
\p
\v 21 His servantsВҰ147387 \add вүҲqueried\add* him, вҖң\add вүҲWe don't understand what just happened: when the baby was aliveВҰ147397 you fastedВҰ147398 and wept, butВҰ147386 yet when he dies, you get up and have a meal?\add*вҖқ
\p
\v 22 вҖңWhile the child was stillВҰ147408 aliveВҰ147410,вҖқ David \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңI fastedВҰ147411 and I wept, because I \add вүҲthought\add*, вҖҳWho knows? YahwehВҰ147419 might be graciousВҰ147417 to me and let \add *him\add* live.вҖҷ
\v 23 \add вүҲButВҰ147423\add* now \add that\add* he's dead, \add вүҲthere's no more reason\add* to fastвҖ”I can'tВҰ147437 bringВҰ147431 him back againВҰ147432. \add One day\add* I'llВҰ147433 go to him, \add вүҲbutВҰ147423\add* he'll \add вүҲnever\add* come back \add here\add* to me.вҖқ
\v 24 Then DavidВҰ147443 comfortedВҰ147442 his wife Batsheva.
\s1 The birth of Shelomoh
\rem /s1 Solomon Is Born
\s4 Full kingdom
\p Then \add @David\add* wentВҰ147449 to \add @Batsheva\add* and \add вүҲslept\add* with her, and \add in due course\add* she \add вүҲgaveВҰ147453 birthВҰ147453\add* to a son. \add @David\add* he named himВҰ147462 Shelomoh \add (SolomonВҰ147460)\add*, and YahwehВҰ147461 lovedВҰ147462 \add @that boy\add*
\v 25 andВҰ147464 sentВҰ147464 the prophetВҰ147467 NatanВҰ147466 to name him YedidyahВҰ147472\f + \fr 12:25 \ft That name didn't seem to stick because this is the only mention of it in the Bible.\f* \add (which means вҖҳloved by YahwehвҖҷ)\add* for Yahweh's sake.
\s1 David captures Rabbah
\rem /s1 The Ammonites Crushed; David Captures Rabbah
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (1 Chr. 20:1-3)
\p
\v 26 ThenВҰ147483 YoavВҰ147478 foughtВҰ147477 \add вүҲthe AmmonitesВҰ147481\add* atВҰ147479 RabbahВҰ147479 and capturedВҰ147482 \add &their\add* \add вүҲpalace\add*,
\v 27 thenВҰ147488 \add *he\add* sentВҰ147488 messengersВҰ147490 to DavidВҰ147493 to tell him, вҖңI've foughtВҰ147495 againstВҰ147496 RabbahВҰ147496 \add вүҲandВҰ147494\add* I've overthrown the \add вүҲcity's waterВҰ147503 supply\add*.
\v 28 \add вүҲSoВҰ147505\add* now, gatherВҰ147506 the rest of \add вүҲour fighters\add* and lay siege to the city and captureВҰ147515 it. Otherwise I'll \add *do it\add* and thenВҰ147505 \add вүҲit'll be named after me\add*.
\v 29 \add вүҲSoВҰ147527\add* DavidВҰ147528 gatheredВҰ147527 all his warriors and wentВҰ147534 to RabbahВҰ147535, \add where\add* he attacked \add @the city\add* and capturedВҰ147538 it.
\v 30 \add *He\add* tookВҰ147540 the king's crownВҰ147543 off his head (it was goldВҰ147550 and weighedВҰ147548 around 30kg), and \add вүҲit was placed\add* on \add *his\add* head. \add вүҲAВҰ147557 lot of other plunderВҰ147558 was also taken from\add* the cityВҰ147559.
\v 31 The inhabitants of \add @Rabbah\add* were broughtВҰ147570 out and \add вүҲassignedВҰ147571 to work atВҰ147569 the brickВҰ147579 kiln\add* withВҰ147569 saws, iron picksВҰ147573, and axesВҰ147575. (He did thatВҰ147567 to all the \add вүҲAmmonite\add* citiesВҰ147584.) ThenВҰ147564 DavidВҰ147589 and all his people returnedВҰ147588 to YerushalemВҰ147593.
\c 13
\s1 Amnon rapes Tamar
\rem /s1 Amnon and Tamar; Conflict in David's family; The Rape of Tamar
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲSomeВҰ147612 time afterwardsВҰ147597,\add* David'sВҰ147603 son AmnonВҰ147609 \add вүҲfell in loveВҰ147608 with his beautifulВҰ147605 half-sister\add* TamarВҰ147607 (Abshalom'sВҰ147600 sister),
\v 2 andВҰ147623 \add *he\add* \add вүҲmade himselfВҰ147616 frustratedВҰ147614,\add* \add always thinking about her\add* becauseВҰ147617 sheВҰ147622 was a virginВҰ147621. HoweverВҰ147618, \add *he\add* \add вүҲcouldn't do anythingВҰ147628 withВҰ147617 her\add*.
\v 3 \add вүҲButВҰ147630\add* AmnonВҰ147639 had a very shrewdВҰ147641 friendВҰ147631 called YonadabВҰ147633 (son of David'sВҰ147638 brotherВҰ147637 ShimeahВҰ147636)
\v 4 andВҰ147658 \add @Yonadab\add* \add вүҲasked\add* him, вҖң\add Hey,\add* \add вүҲyou're a son of the kingВҰ147652, so tell me why you're always so unhappy\add*?вҖқ
\p вҖңI'm inВҰ147653 love withВҰ147653 my brotherВҰ147666 Abshalom'sВҰ147665 sisterВҰ147664 TamarВҰ147663,вҖқ AmnonВҰ147660 \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\p
\v 5 вҖң\add вүҲGo to bed\add* and pretendВҰ147677 to be sick,вҖқ YonadabВҰ147672 \add вүҲsuggested\add*. вҖңThenВҰ147670 \add when\add* your father comesВҰ147678 to see you, \add вүҲask\add* him, вҖҳPlease let my sisterВҰ147686 TamarВҰ147685 comeВҰ147683 \add вүҲto look after my food. She can cook it here and serve it to me\add*.вҖҷ вҖқ
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ147700\add* Amnon lay down and pretendedВҰ147702 to be sick, and \add when\add* the king came to see him, Amnon \add вүҲasked\add* \add *him\add*, вҖңPlease, let my sisterВҰ147715 TamarВҰ147714 come and make a couple of breadВҰ147716 rolls \add вүҲwhile I'm watching, and thenВҰ147700 she can serve them to me\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲSoВҰ147723\add* DavidВҰ147724 sentВҰ147723 \add a message\add* to TamarВҰ147727 \add вүҲto ask her to\add* goВҰ147730 to her brotherВҰ147734 Amnon'sВҰ147733 houseВҰ147732 andВҰ147723 prepareВҰ147735 food for him.
\v 8 \add вүҲSoВҰ147740\add* TamarВҰ147741 wentВҰ147740 to herВҰ147744 half-brother Amnon'sВҰ147743 houseВҰ147742 where he was lyingВҰ147746 down. She tookВҰ147747 \add вүҲsome\add* doughВҰ147750 and kneaded it into breadrolls and bakedВҰ147755 them.
\v 9 ThenВҰ147760 she tookВҰ147760 the tray \add вүҲover to him\add*, butВҰ147760 he refusedВҰ147766 to eatВҰ147767, saying, вҖң\add вүҲSendВҰ147761 everyone else out of here\add*,вҖқ \add вүҲso they all leftВҰ147764\add*.
\v 10 ThenВҰ147781 Amnon told Tamar, вҖңBring the food into the bedroom so that \add вүҲyou can serve it to me\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ147781\add* Tamar took the breadrolls that she'd made, andВҰ147781 took them to Amnon in the bedroom.
\v 11 \add вүҲButВҰ147803 when she got close enough to him,\add* he grabbed herВҰ147808 and insisted, вҖңComeВҰ147814 \add and\add* lie down withВҰ147808 me, my sisterВҰ147814.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 вҖңNo, my brotherВҰ147820,вҖқ she told him, вҖңdon't humiliate me because \add вүҲwe Israelis don't do that\add*. Don't do this disgracefulВҰ147835 thingВҰ147835.
\v 13 Where \add вүҲcould I hide my shame\add*? And youвҖ”you'd be \add вүҲconsidered\add* a godless fool inВҰ147848 YisraelВҰ147848. \add вүҲJust speakВҰ147850 to the kingВҰ147855 because he'd give me to you to marry\add*.вҖқ
\v 14 \add вүҲButВҰ147869 he didn'tВҰ147861 want her advice, and being\add* strongerВҰ147865 than her, he humiliated her \add вүҲby forcing her down and raping\add* her.
\p
\v 15 \add вүҲInstantlyВҰ147887,\add* AmnonВҰ147872 hated her with terrible hatredвҖ”a much greater hatred than the love with which he'd lovedВҰ147883 her, and \add *he\add* told her to get up and get out.
\p
\v 16 вҖңNo, \add no\add*.вҖқ she respondedВҰ147891. вҖң\add вүҲSending me away would be even worse than what you just\add* did to me.вҖқ
\p \add вүҲButВҰ147891\add* he refused to listenВҰ147907 to her
\v 17 and calledВҰ147910 hisВҰ147914 \add вүҲpersonal servant\add*. He told himВҰ147914 to \add вүҲtake\add* the woman away and sendВҰ147916 her outsideВҰ147923 and thenВҰ147910 lock the doorВҰ147925 behindВҰ147926 her.
\v 18 (SheВҰ147940 was wearing the kind of longВҰ147929 robe that the virginВҰ147937 daughtersВҰ147934 of the kingВҰ147936 wore as an outer garmentВҰ147929.)
\p \add вүҲSoВҰ147928 the servantВҰ147941 pushed\add* her outsideВҰ147942 andВҰ147928 lockedВҰ147943 the doorВҰ147944 behindВҰ147945 her.
\v 19 ThenВҰ147947 TamarВҰ147948 put ashes on her head and tore the longВҰ147953 robeВҰ147953 thatВҰ147955 she was wearing. She put her hand on her head and wailed as she walked \add home\add*.\f + \fr 13:19 \ft The ashes, tearing of clothes, putting hand on head, and wailing, were all cultural signs of mourning and distress.\f*
\v 20 HerВҰ147970 brother Abshalom \add вүҲasked\add* her, вҖң\add вүҲDid your half-brother AmnonВҰ147971 mess\add* with you? ButВҰ147967 now, my sisterВҰ147976, \add вүҲdon't tell anyone since he's your brother andВҰ147967 don't let it upset you\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ147967\add* TamarВҰ147989 lived \add вүҲin a state of desolationВҰ147990\add* in her brother Abshalom'sВҰ147969 houseВҰ147991.
\p
\v 21 \add вүҲWhenВҰ147995\add* KingВҰ147995 DavidВҰ147996 heardВҰ147997 about all that, \add вүҲhe got very angry\add*.
\v 22 \add Also,\add* AbshalomВҰ148010 said nothing to AmnonВҰ148013 (eitherВҰ148014 goodВҰ148017 or badВҰ148014) because he hatedВҰ148020 \add *him\add* for humiliating his sisterВҰ148032 TamarВҰ148031.
\s1 Abshalom kills Amnon
\rem /s1 Absalom Avenges the Violation of His Sister; Absalom's Revenge; Absalom Kills Amnon; Absalom's Revenge on Amnon
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 23 Two yearsВҰ148036 passed, then Abshalom'sВҰ148040 shearersВҰ148039 were inВҰ148041 Baal-Hatsor (near EfrayimВҰ148046) and Abshalom \add вүҲinvited\add* all the king'sВҰ148052 sonsВҰ148051.
\v 24 AbshalomВҰ148055 went to the king and \add вүҲasked\add* him, вҖңListen, please, \add вүҲthe shearersВҰ148063 are working for\add* your servant. Please, let the king and his servants come with your servant.вҖқ
\p
\v 25 вҖңNo, my son,вҖқ the kingВҰ148075 \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖң\add вүҲThere's too many of usвҖ”it would be too expensive\add* for you.вҖқ \add @Abshalom\add* he urgedВҰ148090 him, butВҰ148074 he wouldn't go, \add вүҲhowever\add* he did blessВҰ148097 him.
\p
\v 26 вҖңButВҰ148099 if \add you don'tВҰ148101 come\add*,вҖқ AbshalomВҰ148100 \add вүҲinsisted\add*, вҖңpleaseВҰ148104 let my brotherВҰ148107 AmnonВҰ148106 come with us.вҖқ
\p вҖңWhy shouldВҰ148102 \em he\em* go with you?вҖқ the kingВҰ148110 \add вүҲasked\add*.
\v 27 \add вүҲButВҰ148115\add* AbshalomВҰ148118 \add вүҲinsisted, so\add* \add @the kingВҰ148128\add* \add agreed to\add* send AmnonВҰ148123 andВҰ148115 \add *his\add* other sonsВҰ148127.
\v 28 Then AbshalomВҰ148132 \add вүҲprepared\add* his young men, вҖңListen now, when Amnon \add вүҲgets a bit drunk from\add* the wine and I tell you all, вҖҳStrike Amnon!вҖҷ then you'll killВҰ148150 him. You all don'tВҰ148152 \add need to\add* be afraidВҰ148154 \add because\add* I myself am the one commanding you. Be courageous \add вүҲwarriors\add*.вҖқ
\v 29 \add At the right time,\add* Abshalom'sВҰ148168 servantsВҰ148167 did to AmnonВҰ148169 what Abshalom commandedВҰ148171 \add <them\add*. All the rest of the king's sonsВҰ148177 \add вүҲjumped\add* up and onto their mules and fled \add away\add*.
\p
\v 30 \add вүҲWhileВҰ148197 theyВҰ148187 were still onВҰ148188 the wayВҰ148188\add*, DavidВҰ148193 heard the newsВҰ148189 that AbshalomВҰ148196 had struckВҰ148195 all of his sonsВҰ148201 and killed them, and none were left alive.
\v 31 The kingВҰ148211 \add вүҲstood\add* up and tore his clothes, then he laid down on the groundВҰ148217. \add Meanwhile\add*, all his servantsВҰ148220 \add there\add* were tearing their clothes.
\v 32 Then YonadabВҰ148227 (David'sВҰ148234 brotherВҰ148232 Shimeah'sВҰ148231 son) \add вүҲspokeВҰ148226 up\add*, вҖңMy masterВҰ148239, don'tВҰ148236 \add вүҲimagine that\add* all those youngВҰ148243 menВҰ148243, the king's sonsВҰ148244, have been murdered. \add I suspect that\add* only AmnonВҰ148250 is dead, because AbshalomВҰ148258 \add вүҲhas been determinedВҰ148260 to do this ever since\add* his sisterВҰ148265 TamarВҰ148264 was humiliated.
\v 33 \add вүҲSoВҰ148267 my masterВҰ148271, don'tВҰ148268 believe the report that all your\add* sonsВҰ148280 are dead. \add вүҲIt's probably\add* only AmnonВҰ148287 who's dead.
\p
\v 34 \add Meanwhile,\add* AbshalomВҰ148293 had fled.
\p \add Suddenly\add* the watchmanВҰ148296 \add вүҲturned\add* and sawВҰ148301, wow, many peopleВҰ148303 comingВҰ148306 around the hillВҰ148310 along the roadВҰ148307 behindВҰ148308 himВҰ148308.
\v 35 вҖңLook,вҖқ YonadabВҰ148313 told the king. вҖңThe king's sons are coming! \add вүҲIt's just what I said\add*.вҖқ
\v 36 He'd \add hardly\add* finishedВҰ148329 speakingВҰ148330 when, wow, the king's sons came in. ThenВҰ148327 they all cried loudly, and the king and his servantsВҰ148344 \add вүҲjoined them in theirВҰ148337 wailing\add*.
\p
\v 37 \add вүҲBut\add* AbshalomВҰ148350 \add had\add* fled, andВҰ148350 he wentВҰ148352 to GeshurВҰ148361 to stay with KingВҰ148360 Ammihud'sВҰ148358 son, TalmayВҰ148355. \add вүҲBut\add* \add @David\add* mournedВҰ148362 for his son every day.\x + \xo 13:37: \xt 2Sam 3:3.\x*
\v 38 \add вүҲAfter\add* AbshalomВҰ148370 fled to GeshurВҰ148373, heВҰ148371 stayed thereВҰ148376 for threeВҰ148377 yearsВҰ148378.
\v 39 \add By thenВҰ148380,\add* KingВҰ148382 DavidВҰ148381 was \add вүҲno longer grieving over Amnon'sВҰ148392 death\add* andВҰ148380 longed to goВҰ148383 to \add see\add* AbshalomВҰ148386.
\c 14
\s1 Abshalom returns to Yerushalem
\rem /s1 Joab Arranges for Absalom's Return; Absalom Returns to Jerusalem
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲNow\add* YoavВҰ148399 (Tseruyah's son) \add вүҲrealised\add* that the kingВҰ148406 \add вүҲmissed\add* AbshalomВҰ148409,
\v 2 \add вүҲso\add* he sent for a wise woman from TekoaВҰ148413 and told her, вҖңNow, please put on mourning clothesВҰ148426 and don'tВҰ148429 \add вүҲput on any make-up\add*. \add вүҲAct\add* like a woman who has been mourning for the dead for \add вүҲseveral\add* daysВҰ148436,
\v 3 and go to the king and \add вүҲgive him this messageВҰ148449\add*.вҖқ ThenВҰ148443 YoavВҰ148452 told herВҰ148456 what to say to the king.
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ148458\add* the Tekoan womanВҰ148459 went to the king andВҰ148458 \add вүҲfell onto herВҰ148467 knees with his faceВҰ148467 down to the ground\add*, saying, вҖң\add вүҲYour majesty, help\add* \add me\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 вҖңWhat's \add вүҲthe matter\add*?вҖқ the kingВҰ148478 \add вүҲasked\add*.
\p вҖңAlas, I'm a widowВҰ148486,вҖқ she \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖңMy husbandВҰ148489 has diedВҰ148488.
\v 6 Your female servantВҰ148491 had two sonsВҰ148493, and the two of them foughtВҰ148494 \add each other out\add* in the countrysideВҰ148496. There wasn't anyoneВҰ148501 thereВҰ148497 who could \add вүҲstop\add* them, and thenВҰ148491 one \add son\add* struckВҰ148500 the other and killedВҰ148505 him.
\v 7 \add вүҲNow\add* listen, the entireВҰ148510 clan has \add вүҲturned against\add* your female servantВҰ148515 and \add вүҲdemanded\add*, вҖҳGive \add <us\add* the one who \add вүҲkilled\add* his brother, and we'll killВҰ148528 him inВҰ148524 exchange for the lifeВҰ148524 of the brother that he killed. Also, \add вүҲit would mean that this evil thing couldn't be passed onВҰ148524\add*.вҖҷ \add вүҲButВҰ148508 that would leave me withВҰ148524 no descendants to continue\add* my husband'sВҰ148543 nameВҰ148544.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 вҖңGoВҰ148559 \add вүҲhome\add*,вҖқ the kingВҰ148553 told the womanВҰ148556, вҖңand I'llВҰ148560 \add вүҲmake a decision about what to do\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 9 \add вүҲButВҰ148563\add* the Tekoan womanВҰ148564 \add вүҲcontinuedВҰ148563\add*, вҖңThe \add вүҲblame\add*,\f + \fr 14:9 \ft Presumably for not putting the murderer to death.\f* my masterВҰ148570 the king, \add вүҲwill be on me and my extended family, butВҰ148563\add* the king and his throneВҰ148578 will be innocentВҰ148579.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 вҖңAnyoneВҰ148584 who speaksВҰ148584 againstВҰ148591 you,вҖқ saidВҰ148582 the kingВҰ148583, вҖңbringВҰ148586 them to me, and then they won'tВҰ148588 \add вүҲtrouble\add* you any more.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 вҖңPlease,вҖқ she \add вүҲinsisted\add*, вҖңmay the kingВҰ148599 \add вүҲask\add* your godВҰ148603 Yahweh to prevent the avengerВҰ148606 of bloodВҰ148607 from increasingВҰ148604 the \add вүҲtragedy\add*, so my son won'tВҰ148609 be destroyedВҰ148610.вҖқ
\p вҖңAs surely as Yahweh lives,вҖқ he \add вүҲvowed\add*, вҖңnot a hair from your son's head will fall to the groundВҰ148623.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 ThenВҰ148625 the womanВҰ148626 said, вҖңPlease, let your female servantВҰ148630 \add вүҲask\add* my masterВҰ148633 the kingВҰ148634 \add вүҲa question\add*.вҖқ
\p вҖңSpeak,вҖқ he \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\p
\v 13 \add вүҲSo\add* the womanВҰ148641 \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖңWhy have you \add вүҲacted\add* like this against God's peopleВҰ148647? When the king says that \add to me\add*, isn'tВҰ148654 he convicting himself since he hasn't \add вүҲbrought back\add* \em his own\em* \add вүҲbanishedВҰ148659 son\add*?
\v 14 \add вүҲIt's certainВҰ148663 that we'll\add* \add all\add* die. Water that's spilt on the ground can'tВҰ148669 be gathered together \add again\add* \add вүҲbutВҰ148665\add* God's \add not like that\add*. Rather than taking away lifeВҰ148675, he devisesВҰ148676 plansВҰ148677 so that the one who was banishedВҰ148681 can be \add вүҲgathered back in\add*.
\v 15 \add The reason\add* that I'veВҰ148686 come now to tell this to the king my masterВҰ148691, is because the peopleВҰ148698 have frightened me. \add вүҲSoВҰ148683\add* your servant said \add to herself\add*, вҖҳI will speakВҰ148701, pleaseВҰ148703, to the king. Perhaps the king will \add вүҲhonour the request\add* of his female servant.
\v 16 \add вүҲMaybe\add* the kingВҰ148717 will listenВҰ148716 in order to save his female servantВҰ148721 from the manВҰ148723 who's \add вүҲcutting\add* me andВҰ148726 my son togetherВҰ148729 \add off\add* from the inheritanceВҰ148730 given by GodВҰ148731.вҖҷ
\v 17 And your female servantВҰ148734 \add вүҲthought\add*, вҖҳPlease, let the word of my master the king becomeВҰ148735 \add вүҲmy assurance\add*, because my master the king is like God's messengerВҰ148738 \add when it comes to\add* understanding good andВҰ148733 evil. And may YahwehВҰ148740 your godВҰ148754 be with you.вҖҷ вҖқ\x + \xo 14:17: \xt 2Sam 19:27.\x*
\p
\v 18 вҖң\add Hang on,\add*вҖқ the king told the woman. вҖң\add вүҲI want you to answerВҰ148759 this question honestly\add*.вҖқ
\p вҖңPlease, let my masterВҰ148780 the king speakВҰ148777.вҖқ \add *she\add* \add вүҲrespondedВҰ148761\add*.
\p
\v 19 вҖң\add вүҲDid Yoav perhaps have anything to do\add* withВҰ148819 all this?вҖқ he \add вүҲasked\add*.
\p The womanВҰ148792 answeredВҰ148791, вҖңBy the life of your spirit, my master the king, there'sВҰ148801 no \add вүҲavoiding anything\add* that my master the king has said. \add Yes,\add* your servant YoavвҖ”he himself commandedВҰ148816 me, andВҰ148783 he himself \add вүҲtoldВҰ148816\add* your female servant \add вүҲwhat I should say\add*.
\v 20 Your servantВҰ148834 YoavВҰ148835 \add вүҲset this up to try to remedy the situationВҰ148832\add*. ButВҰ148840 my masterВҰ148840 is wise like the wisdomВҰ148842 of one of God's messengersВҰ148843 to knowВҰ148845 everything that's \add going on here\add* on earthВҰ148851.вҖқ
\p
\v 21 Then the kingВҰ148855 \add summoned\add* YoavВҰ148858 and told him, вҖң\add вүҲAll right then,\add* I'll \add вүҲsort this out. Now\add* goВҰ148867 \add and\add* bringВҰ148868 back the youngВҰ148871 manВҰ148871 AbshalomВҰ148874.вҖқ
\p
\v 22 YoavВҰ148877 fell \add вүҲonto his knees and bowedВҰ148882\add* his face to the ground, and blessedВҰ148883 the king, thenВҰ148876 he said, вҖңToday, your servant knowsВҰ148890 that I have foundВҰ148894 favourВҰ148895 inВҰ148896 your eyesВҰ148896, my masterВҰ148897 the king, since the king \add вүҲis going to do what\add* his servant \add вүҲasked\add*.вҖқ
\v 23 ThenВҰ148909 YoavВҰ148910 got up and wentВҰ148911 to GeshurВҰ148912 to get AbshalomВҰ148916 and bring him \add back\add* to YerushalemВҰ148917,
\v 24 \add вүҲbut\add* the king said, вҖңHe can go around to his house, but he's \add вүҲto stay right away from me\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲSo\add* AbshalomВҰ148930 \add вүҲlived in his own\add* house, \add вүҲbut wasn't allowed into the palace\add*.
