\v 30 \add вүҲso\add* he \add вүҲinstructed\add* his servants, вҖңListen, Yoav's \add вүҲpiece of land withВҰ149052 a barley crop is nearby\add*. Go andВҰ149035 set fire to it.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ149035\add* Abshalom's servants \add вүҲburnt\add* \add @Yoav's barley\add*.\f + \fr 14:30 \ft TC: The Septuagint translation adds the following words here: вҖңAnd Abshalom's servants burnt them up. Then Yoav's servants came to him, tearing their garments. They saidвҖҰвҖқ\f*
\p
\v 31 Then YoavВҰ149063 wentВҰ149064 to Abshalom'sВҰ149067 houseВҰ149068 and \add вүҲdemanded\add*, вҖңWhy did yourВҰ149073 servantsВҰ149073 \add вүҲdestroy my barley crop\add*?вҖқ
