\p
\v 1 \add вүҲSometime afterВҰ149152 all that\add*, AbshalomВҰ149156 \add вүҲacquired\add* a chariotВҰ149157 and horsesВҰ149158 and \add hired\add* fiftyВҰ149159 men to run aheadВҰ149162 of himВҰ149162.
\v 2 \add *He\add* would get up earlyВҰ149164 and standВҰ149166 \add вүҲon the side of the road going in and out of the city\add*. \add вүҲEveryВҰ149201 time that someone came into the city to take a dispute to be settled by the king, AbshalomВҰ149165 would ask them whereВҰ149192 they were from, and they'd reply with their city and tribeВҰ149199\add*,
\v 3 thenВҰ149204 \add *he'd\add* say, вҖңListen, \add No doubt\add* what you're saying is sensible andВҰ149204 rightВҰ149210, butВҰ149204 the kingВҰ149216 hasn't \add вүҲappointed anyoneВҰ149211 to listenВҰ149211 to people from yourВҰ149208 area\add*.вҖқ
\v 4 ThenВҰ149218 AbshalomВҰ149219 would \add вүҲadd\add*, вҖң\add вүҲIf I was\add* appointedВҰ149222 as judgeВҰ149223, thenВҰ149218 everyВҰ149227 personВҰ149229 with a dispute or case could comeВҰ149226 to me andВҰ149218 \add вүҲobtain\add* justiceВҰ149238.вҖқ
\v 5 WheneverВҰ149247 anyoneВҰ149243 approached him to \add вүҲbow respectfully\add* to him, he would put out his handВҰ149249 and \add вүҲembrace\add* them and kissВҰ149252 them.
\v 6 AbshalomВҰ149256 acted \add вүҲthat wayВҰ149257 towards every Israeli\add* who cameВҰ149264 for \add вүҲa dispute to be settled by\add* the kingВҰ149268, andВҰ149255 \add in doing that\add* he stoleВҰ149269 the \add #hearts\add* of the \add вүҲIsraeli people\add*.
\p
\v 7 Four\f + \fr 15:7 \ft The Hebrew says forty years, but this is interpreted here as a scribal error. (David's entire reign was only forty years, see 1 Kings 2:11.)\f* years \add вүҲlater,\add* AbshalomВҰ149283 \add вүҲbegged\add* the kingВҰ149286, вҖңPlease, \add вүҲrelease me to\add* goВҰ149287 and fulfill the vow thatВҰ149293 I made to YahwehВҰ149296 inВҰ149297 HebronВҰ149297,
\v 8 because when I was living in GeshurВҰ149305 (in AramВҰ149306) \add вүҲI promised YahwehВҰ149313 that\add* if heВҰ149302 brought me \add back\add* to YerushalemВҰ149314, then I'd worshipВҰ149315 him \add in Hebron\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 9 вҖңGo inВҰ149325 peaceВҰ149325,вҖқ the kingВҰ149323 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ149320, so\add* Abshalom \add вүҲleft for\add* HebronВҰ149328.
\v 10 \add From there,\add* \add *he\add* sentВҰ149331 \add вүҲsleeper groups\add* into all \add areas\add* of YisraelВҰ149337, telling \add <them\add*, вҖңWhen youВҰ149339 all hearВҰ149339 the trumpetВҰ149343 blasts, then \add вүҲshout\add*, вҖҳAbshalomВҰ149332 has becomeВҰ149345 kingВҰ149345 from HebronВҰ149347!вҖҷ вҖқ
