\v 18 ThenВҰ149481 all his servantsВҰ149483 passed beside him to go ahead, along withВҰ149504 his bodyguards (the KerethitesВҰ149490 and the Felethites) and six hundredВҰ149499 Gittites (from Gat).
\v 19 ThenВҰ149512 the king said to IttaiВҰ149516 the GittiteВҰ149517, вҖң\add вүҲYou don't have to come\add* with us. You're a foreignerВҰ149531 and an exileВҰ149535 from your placeВҰ149537, \add вүҲso you could\add* go back and stay with the \add new\add* king.
\v 20 \add вүҲYou haven't been here long\add*, and we don't even know whereВҰ149550 we're going. \add вүҲI certainly need to leave butВҰ149542 you can returnВҰ149554 with your relatives\add*. \add May Yahweh show\add* kindness and faithfulnessВҰ149561 \add to you all\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 21 вҖң\add вүҲAsВҰ149571 YahwehВҰ149573 lives, andВҰ149563 as my master the king lives\add*,вҖқ IttaiВҰ149564 answeredВҰ149563 the king, вҖң\add вүҲwhereverВҰ149579 my master the king goes\add*, your servantВҰ149596 will certainly be there \add also\add*, whetherВҰ149586 \add вүҲit means life or deathВҰ149588\add*.вҖқ
