\v 22 вҖң\add Okay,\add* go \add вүҲahead thenВҰ149598\add*,вҖқ David told Ittai. \add вүҲSoВҰ149598\add* Ittai and all his menВҰ149610 and \add вүҲtheir families went with David\add*.
\v 23 \add вүҲAll the people along the road cried when they saw them walking by\add*. The kingВҰ149627 and all the others crossed the KidronВҰ149630 riverbed and went up the hill toward the wildernessВҰ149642.
\p
\v 24 \add вүҲWhat a sight!\add* Even TsadokВҰ149647 and all the LevitesВҰ149650 with him were carryingВҰ149652 the boxВҰ149655 with God's agreement \add in it\add*, and when they put it down \add again\add*, \add the priest\add* Evyatar caught up \add to them and waited\add* untilВҰ149665 all the peopleВҰ149670 had finishedВҰ149667 \add exiting\add* the cityВҰ149674.
\v 25 \add вүҲButВҰ149676\add* the kingВҰ149677 told TsadokВҰ149678, вҖң\add вүҲTake the sacred chestВҰ149682 back into\add* the cityВҰ149684. If YahwehВҰ149690 favoursВҰ149688 me, thenВҰ149676 he'll \add вүҲhelp\add* me return, and he'll \add вүҲlet\add* me seeВҰ149692 it and his \add вүҲplaceВҰ149696 of residence\add* \add again\add*.
\v 26 \add вүҲButВҰ149698\add* if \add @Yahweh\add* says that he isn'tВҰ149701 pleased withВҰ149710 me, thenВҰ149698 he'll do to me \add вүҲwhatever he thinks best\add*.
