\p
\v 5 \add вүҲWhenВҰ150001\add* KingВҰ150002 David got to BahurimВҰ150006, wow, a manВҰ150009 from Sha'ul's \add вүҲextended familyВҰ150011\add* came out. He was Gera'sВҰ150019 son ShimeiВҰ150016, and he came out and cursed \add <David\add*.
\v 6 ThenВҰ150024 he threw stonesВҰ150025 atВҰ150025 DavidВҰ150028 and all \add *his\add* servantsВҰ150033, and all the peopleВҰ150038 and \add вүҲwarriors\add* onВҰ150025 \add вүҲboth sides\add* of \add @the kingВҰ150034\add*.
\v 7 вҖңGoВҰ150052 away, go away, you worthlessВҰ150055 man of \add вүҲmuch bloodshedВҰ150053\add*!вҖқ ShimeiВҰ150048 \add вүҲyelled\add*.
\v 8 вҖң\add Now\add* Yahweh's returning to you all the blood of Sha'ul's householdВҰ150063. You \add вүҲtook over as\add* king inВҰ150075 hisВҰ150068 placeВҰ150068, \add вүҲbutВҰ150070\add* Yahweh's giving the kingdom into the handВҰ150075 of yourВҰ150079 son AbshalomВҰ150076. Look atВҰ150075 you, you're evil because you're a manВҰ150081 of \add вүҲmuch bloodshed\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 9 The Tseruyah's son AbishaiВҰ150086 \add вүҲasked\add* the king, вҖңWhy shouldВҰ150102 this dead dog curseВҰ150094 my masterВҰ150100 the king? Please, let me crossВҰ150102 over andВҰ150085 \add вүҲlop off\add* his headВҰ150108.вҖқ
