\v 10 ThenВҰ150566 \add вүҲeven your bravest warriors might lose heart\add*, because all YisraelВҰ150583 knows that your father is a \add вүҲpowerful warrior\add*, andВҰ150566 \add also\add* that the men with him are \add вүҲvery experienced\add*.
\v 11 \add вүҲSo this is what I suggest\add*: \add вүҲCall warriors from\add* all YisraelВҰ150601вҖ”from DanВҰ150602 \add in the far north\add* to BeerВҰ150605-Sheva \add in the far south\add*. They'll be as numerous as sand \add grains\add* onВҰ150616 the beach and youВҰ150598 \add вүҲpersonallyВҰ150614 will be able to lead them into\add* battleВҰ150616.
\v 12 ThenВҰ150618 we'll \add вүҲbe able to find him whereverВҰ150623 he is\add*, and \add вүҲattack him like dew blankets the entireВҰ150638 area\add*, and neither him nor any of the menВҰ150640 withВҰ150620 him \add вүҲwill survive\add*, not even one.
\v 13 IfВҰ150657 he \add вүҲescaped into some\add* city, \add вүҲwe'd all\add* bringВҰ150654 ropesВҰ150662 to that city andВҰ150648 drag \add @the stones\add* into the valleyВҰ150667 untilВҰ150668 even a pebbleВҰ150677 couldn't be foundВҰ150673 thereВҰ150674.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 Abshalom and all the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ150684 elders agreed that Hushay's advice was better than Ahitofel's\add*. (YahwehВҰ150702 had \add вүҲinfluenced\add* them to reject Ahitofel's good advice so \add *he\add* could bringВҰ150701 disaster onto Abshalom.)
\s1 The warning to David to flee
