\v 4 вҖңI'llВҰ151131 do whatever seems best to you,вҖқ the king \add вүҲrespondedВҰ151124\add*. \add вүҲSo\add* the king stayed beside the city gateВҰ151137 while the \add вүҲmen\add* went out by their hundredsВҰ151142 and thousandsВҰ151143.
\v 5 ThenВҰ151145 he commanded YoavВҰ151149 and AbishaiВҰ151152 and IttaiВҰ151155, вҖң\add вүҲFor my sake, don't harm my son\add* Abshalom.вҖқ All the peopleВҰ151164 heardВҰ151165 the king \add вүҲgive this command\add* about Abshalom \add вүҲto all the leaders\add*.
