\v 9 AbshalomВҰ151229 happenedВҰ151228 to meet some of David'sВҰ151232 \add вүҲmen\add*. \add *He\add* was ridingВҰ151234 his mule, and when \add it\add* \add вүҲdarted\add* under the think branches of a large terebinth \add treeВҰ151246\add*, his headВҰ151245 got caughtВҰ151244 in the branches and he was \add вүҲleft hangingВҰ151247 in the air\add* as the mule \add вүҲkept going\add*.
\v 10 \add вүҲSomeoneВҰ151265 noticedВҰ151258 him\add* andВҰ151258 informed YoavВҰ151262 that he'd seen AbshalomВҰ151268 hanging inВҰ151270 a treeВҰ151270.
\p
\v 11 вҖң\add вүҲWhat!\add*. You sawВҰ151278 \add <him\add* \add вүҲbutВҰ151272 didn'tВҰ151280 strikeВҰ151282 him down\add*?вҖқ YoavВҰ151273 \add вүҲchallenged\add*. вҖң\add вүҲI would have given\add* youВҰ151278 tenВҰ151288 silverВҰ151289 \add coins\add* andВҰ151272 a \add leather\add* beltВҰ151290.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 вҖңEven if \add вүҲyou'd placed one thousandВҰ151306 silverВҰ151307 coins inВҰ151318 my hands\add*,вҖқ \add *he\add* \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңI wouldn't have \add вүҲharmed\add* the king's son, because \add вүҲwe heard the king's commandВҰ151319 withВҰ151318 ourВҰ151318 own earsВҰ151318 about looking out for\add* AbshalomВҰ151333.
\v 13 \add вүҲEven if I'd ignored my good sense, the kingВҰ151349 would have found out about itВҰ151346, then even youВҰ151351 wouldn't have stood up for\add* me.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 вҖң\add вүҲI'mВҰ151359 not going to waste time arguing withВҰ151364 you\add*,вҖқ YoavВҰ151355 respondedВҰ151354, thenВҰ151354 he tookВҰ151361 threeВҰ151362 spearsВҰ151363 \add and went\add* and thrustВҰ151365 them into Abshalom'sВҰ151367 \add вүҲabdomen\add* whileВҰ151368 he was \add вүҲstillВҰ151368 aliveВҰ151369 and dangling from the treeВҰ151371\add*.
