\s4 Full kingdom
\p \add вүҲButВҰ151925 Abshalom's warriors had all returned to their homes\add*
\v 9 and \add вүҲover time\add*, people \add вүҲall across\add* YisraelВҰ151982 began to quarrel and say, вҖңThe king rescued us from the \add вүҲplans\add* of our enemies \add вүҲincludingВҰ151963\add* the Philistines, butВҰ151963 now he's \add вүҲleft IsraelВҰ151982\add* and fled away from Abshalom.
\v 10 We anointed AbshalomВҰ152014 to be over us, butВҰ151989 he died in the battle. So why \add вүҲaren't we doing something\add* about returning \add David as\add* kingВҰ151999?вҖқ
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲSo\add* KingВҰ152030 David sent the \add two\add* priests Tsadok and Evyatar to the leaders of Yehudah \add вүҲto ask\add*, вҖңWhy are you the last \add >group\add* to return the king to \add вүҲthe palace since the king has heard that the rest of Yisrael want it\add*?
\v 12 \add Tell them,\add* вҖҳYou're all my relativesвҖ”my own flesh and blood, \add вүҲso\add* why \add would\add* youВҰ152052 be the last to \add вүҲsupport me\add* \add again\add*?вҖҷ вҖқ
\v 13 And tell Amasa, вҖҳAren't you my \add own\add* fleshВҰ152077 and bone? May God \add вүҲmake me suffer\add* if you don't become my army commander \add вүҲfrom now on, to replace\add* Yoav.вҖҷ вҖқ
\v 14 \add In that way,\add* \add @David\add* \add вүҲunited all the people\add* of Yehudah and they \add вүҲnotified\add* the king, вҖң\add We all want\add* you and all your servants to return \add here\add*.вҖқ
\rem /s1 David's Return to Jerusalem
\p
\v 15 \add вүҲSo\add* the king \add вүҲheaded back\add* and reached the Yordan River, and \add men from\add* YehudahВҰ152124 went to Gilgal to meet the king and \add вүҲhelp\add* \add *him\add* across.
\p
\v 16 Shimei (son of Gera the Benyaminite from Bahurim) hurried down with the Yehudah men to meet KingВҰ152139 David.\x + \xo 19:16: \xt 2Sam 16:5-13.\x*
\v 17 A thousand Benyamite men \add вүҲcame\add* with him, as well as Tsiva (formerly Sha'ul's servant) and fifteen of his sons and twenty of his servants, and they hurriedВҰ152159 to the Yordan to \add вүҲmeet\add* the kingВҰ152175.
\v 18 They crossed the ford \add to help\add* bring the king's householdВҰ152185 \add back\add* \add вүҲacross\add* and \add вүҲanything else the king wanted\add*.
\s1 David's mercy to Shimei
