\s4 Full kingdom
\p Shimei (Gera's son) fell \add вүҲonto his knees in frontВҰ152195\add* of the king when he crossed the YordanВҰ152194
\v 19 and \add вүҲbegged\add* the king, вҖңMay my master not \add вүҲconsider me guilty\add*, and \add вүҲdon't keep thinking about the terrible thing\add* your servant dig onВҰ152208 the day that my master the king left JerusalemвҖ”\add вүҲdon't brood over it\add*
\v 20 because your servantВҰ152238 knows thatВҰ152236 I myself have sinned, and look, I have come today, first of all the Yosef's clans to come down to meet my master, the king.вҖқ
\p
\v 21 \add вүҲButВҰ152261\add* Abishai (Tseruyah's son) \add вүҲanswered\add* \add instead\add*, вҖң\add вүҲRather than that\add*, shouldn't Shimei be killed because he cursed Yahweh's anointed one?вҖқ
\p
\v 22 вҖңYou sons of Tseruyah!вҖқ David respondedВҰ152277. вҖң\add вүҲWho asked you\add* \add two\add* \add вүҲto accuse others to me today\add*? \add вүҲShould today be a time to kill other Israelis\add*? \add вүҲActually, I think it might be\add* \em me\em* who's Yisrael's king?вҖқ
\v 23 Then the kingВҰ152323 \add вүҲpromised\add* Shimei, вҖңYou won'tВҰ152317 die \add вүҲfor that\add*.вҖқ
\s1 David's mercy to Mefiboshet
\rem /s1 David and Mephibosheth Meet; David's Kindness to Mephibosheth; David Shows Kindness to Mephibosheth
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 24 Then Shaul's \add вүҲgrandson\add* Mefiboshet came down to meet the king. He hadn't \add вүҲshaved\add* or \add вүҲwashed\add* his feet, and he hadn't washed his clothes \add вүҲsince the king had left Yerushalem\add*.\x + \xo 19:24: \xt 2Sam 9:1-13; 16:1-4.\x*
\v 25 He came from Yerushalem down to the Yordan to meet the king who \add вүҲasked\add* him, вҖңWhy didn'tВҰ152349 you not \add вүҲcome\add* withВҰ152373 me, Mefiboshet?вҖқ
\p
\v 26 вҖңMy master the king,вҖқ Mefiboshet \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңmy servant deceived me. I, your servant, had said to get my donkey saddled so I could ride it and go with \add вүҲyou\add*, because \add as you know,\add* your servant is lame.
\v 27 Then my servant \add вүҲlied to you about me\add*. \add вүҲButВҰ152394\add* my masterВҰ152395 the king is like God's messenger, so do \add вүҲwhatever you consider to be appropriate\add*.
\v 28 All my \add вүҲgrandfather's household expected that we'd be executed\add*, yet to placed me, your servantВҰ152419, among those who eat atВҰ152419 your table, \add вүҲso\add* I don't have the right to \add вүҲrequest anything further from\add* the king.вҖқ
\p
\v 29 вҖң\add вүҲSay no more\add*,вҖқ said the king. вҖң\add вүҲThat land will be divided for you and Tsiva\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 30 \add вүҲActually\add*, let him take everything,вҖқ Mefiboshet respondedВҰ152469. вҖң\add вүҲsince\add* my master the king \add вүҲhas been able to return safely\add*.вҖқ
\s1 David's kindness to Barzillai
\rem /s1 David's Kindness to Barzillai; David Shows Kindness to Barzillai
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 31 Barzillai the Gileadite had \add also\add* come down from Rogelim \add вүҲto help\add* the king cross the Yordan.\x + \xo 19:31: \xt 2Sam 17:27-29.\x*
\v 32 At eighty, \add *he\add* was very old, \add вүҲbutВҰ152509 being very wealthy, he'd provided food and supplies\add* to the kingВҰ152516 while he'd stayed atВҰ152521 Mahanayim,
\v 33 \add вүҲso\add* the kingВҰ152537 told \add *him\add*, вҖңYou cross over with me, and I'll provide for you to be with me inВҰ152538 Yerushalem.вҖқ
\p
\v 34 вҖңHow \add вүҲmuch longer am I likely to live\add*?вҖқ BarzillaiВҰ152552 \add вүҲpondered\add*. вҖң\add вүҲWould it really be worth me moving\add* to YerushalemВҰ152559 withВҰ152559 the kingВҰ152549?
\v 35 \add вүҲYour servant is eighty yearsВҰ152569 old\add*. \add вүҲMy mind isn't the same as it was, and I can't really taste what I\add* eat or drink. \add вүҲI can barely hear the sounds\add* of the men and women singing. \add вүҲSo\add* why would your servant become an extra burden to my master the king?вҖқ
\v 36 \add вүҲAs a token privilege\add*, your servant will cross the Yordan with the king, \add вүҲbutВҰ152600\add* why should the king reward me with thatВҰ152598 \add generous\add* reward?
\v 37 Please, let your servant return, and let me die in my city \add вүҲnear\add* the graves of my \add вүҲparents\add*. \add вүҲButВҰ152631\add* look, \add here's\add* your servant KimhamвҖ”let him crossВҰ152623 over with my master the king, and do \add вүҲwhatever you consider to be appropriate\add* for him.вҖқ
\p
\v 38 вҖңKimhamВҰ152651 can crossВҰ152652 over withВҰ152643 me,вҖқ the kingВҰ152656 said, вҖңand I myself will do for him \add вүҲwhatever\add* \em you\em* \add вүҲconsider to be appropriate\add*вҖ”everything thatВҰ152661 you choose concerning me, I'll do for you.вҖқ
\v 39 \add вүҲSo\add* all the people crossed the Yordan, and then the king crossed \add over\add*. The king kissed Barzillai and blessed him, and then \add @Barzillai\add* returned \add вүҲhome\add*.
\s1 Yehudah and Yisrael disagree
\rem /s1 Judah and Israel Argue over the King
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 40 Then the king crossed over to Gilgal, and Kimham crossed over with him. All the people of Yehudah brought the king over and also \add about\add* half of the people of Yisrael.
\rem /s1 An Argument over the King
\v 41 Then, wow, all the men of YisraelВҰ152727 went to the king and \add вүҲdemanded\add*, вҖңWhy did our \add вүҲrelatives\add* from YehudahВҰ152718 \add вүҲsecret\add* you away \add without inviting us\add*? They \add вүҲtook you and your household\add* over the Yordan, and all \add &your\add* men \add вүҲas well\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 42 All the men of YehudahВҰ152747 answered the men of YisraelВҰ152734, вҖңBecause the king is \add from our tribe\add*вҖ”\add вүҲour close relative\add*. \add вүҲWhy should that make you all angry\add*? \add вүҲDo you all think that the king has rewarded us with fancy food or other privileges\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 43 The men of YisraelВҰ152774 answeredВҰ152766 the men of YehudahВҰ152770, вҖң\add Our ten tribes\add* \add вүҲgive us ten shares\add* in the kingвҖ”more than you. \add вүҲSo\add* why \add вүҲdo you look down on us\add*? \add вүҲWeren't we the first to talk about bringing our\add* king back \add to Yerushalem\add*?вҖқ
\p \add вүҲButВҰ152766\add* \add вүҲwhat the men of Yehudah said\add* was harsher than \add вүҲwhat the ten other tribes said\add*.
\c 20
\s1 Sheva rebels against David
\rem /s1 Sheba Rebels Against David; The Revolt of Sheba; Sheba's Rebellion; The Rebellion of Sheba
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲNow there was\add* a good-for-nothing Benyaminite man named Sheva who was Bikri's son, and he blastedВҰ152853 onВҰ152854 the trumpetВҰ152854, then said,
\q1 вҖң\add вүҲWe have no interest\add* in DavidВҰ152860,
\q1 вүҲand no \add вүҲclaim\add* in Yishay'sВҰ152867 son.
\q1 \add вүҲGo home everyВҰ152868 man from\add* YisraelВҰ152870.вҖқ\x + \xo 20:1: \xt 1Ki 12:16; 2Ch 10:16.\x*
\p
\v 2 \add вүҲSoВҰ152872\add* all the men of YisraelВҰ152876 \add вүҲleft\add* DavidВҰ152878 \add вүҲand went with\add* Sheva (Bikri's sons), butВҰ152872 the men of Judah \add вүҲstayed with\add* theirВҰ152887 kingВҰ152887 from the YordanВҰ152890 river and uphill to YerushalemВҰ152893.
\p
\v 3 \add вүҲWhenВҰ152895\add* DavidВҰ152896 \add вүҲgot back\add* to his YerushalemВҰ152900 \add вүҲpalace\add*, the ten slave-wives that he'd \add вүҲleft behind\add* to guard the \add вүҲpalace\add*, \add *he\add* \add вүҲmoved\add* them into a \add separate house\add*. \add That place was\add* guarded andВҰ152895 he providedВҰ152917 for them, butВҰ152895 he didn'tВҰ152919 \add вүҲsleep with\add* themвҖ”\add вүҲthus\add* they were lockedВҰ152923 up untilВҰ152924 \add вүҲthey died livingВҰ152929 as widowsВҰ152928\add*.\x + \xo 20:3: \xt 2Sam 16:22.\x*
\p
\v 4 \add One day\add* the kingВҰ152933 told AmasaВҰ152936 \add (his new army commander)\add*, вҖңSummon the men of YehudahВҰ152944 to \add вүҲbe here in threeВҰ152945 daysВҰ152946, and you be with them\add*.вҖқ
\v 5 \add вүҲSoВҰ152951\add* AmasaВҰ152956 wentВҰ152951 to summonВҰ152953 \add *them\add*, butВҰ152951 he \add вүҲtook longer than the given timeВҰ152961\add*.
\v 6 \add Meanwhile\add* DavidВҰ152967 told AbishaiВҰ152970, вҖңBikri's son Sheva will do more harm to us now than AbshalomВҰ152980. Take \add вүҲsome of my warriors\add* and \add вүҲchase him down\add*, in case he finds \add вүҲsome fortifiedВҰ152994 city to hide in and gets away from us\add*.вҖқ
\v 7 \add вүҲSoВҰ152998 Yoav's menВҰ153000 and the king's bodyguards\add* and all the \add вүҲbest warriorsВҰ153000\add* left YerushalemВҰ153008 to \add вүҲhunt ShebaВҰ153011 down\add*.
\v 8 \add вүҲWhen they were approaching\add* the hugeВҰ153020 rockВҰ153019 atВҰ153022 GibeonВҰ153022, they met AmasaВҰ153023. YoavВҰ153026 was \add вүҲdressed for battle withВҰ153022 a dagger strapped to his waistВҰ153038 under his robe\add*. \add вүҲAs he stepped forwardВҰ153041, he allowed his swordВҰ153034 to drop to the ground\add* \add from his hand\add*.
\v 9 YoavВҰ153046 \add вүҲgreeted\add* Amasa, вҖң\add вүҲIs all well withВҰ153056\add* you, my brotherВҰ153050?вҖқ Then he used his rightВҰ153054 handВҰ153052 to hold Amasa'sВҰ153047 beardВҰ153056 to kissВҰ153058 him,
\v 10 \add вүҲbutВҰ153062\add* Amasa wasn't aware of the dagger thatВҰ153068 was inВҰ153066 Yoav's \add other\add* handВҰ153069. \add @Yoav\add* thrust it into \add &his\add* stomach and his intestines pouredВҰ153077 out onВҰ153066 the ground. There was no need \add to stab him again\add* and \add @Amasa\add* diedВҰ153084 \add right there\add*.
\p ThenВҰ153062 YoavВҰ153071 and his brother AbishaiВҰ153087 \add continued\add* \add вүҲtheir hunt for\add* Bikri's son Sheva.
\v 11 One of Yoav's youngВҰ153099 menВҰ153099 stoodВҰ153097 beside \add @Amasa's body\add* and \add вүҲcalled out\add*, вҖңWhoever favours Yoav and is for DavidВҰ153109, \add вүҲfollow\add* Yoav.вҖқ
\v 12 \add вүҲAmasa'sВҰ153128 bloodyВҰ153115 body\add* was inВҰ153115 the middleВҰ153116 of the road, and when the \add young\add* manВҰ153120 saw that everyoneВҰ153140 was stopping to look atВҰ153115 it, he \add вүҲdragged\add* \add *it\add* off the road onto the \add вүҲgrass\add* and threwВҰ153135 a \add вүҲcloth\add* over it.
\v 13 \add вүҲAfter the body had been removedВҰ153147 from the road,\add* all the men \add вүҲfollowed after\add* YoavВҰ153156 to chase Sheva.
\p
\v 14 \add Meanwhile\add* \add @Sheva\add* crossed through all the \add вүҲtribal regions\add* of YisraelВҰ153168 to AvelВҰ153169-Beyt-Maacah \add вүҲwhere all his relatives gathered together andВҰ153164 agreed to back himВҰ153181\add*.
\v 15 \add @Yoav's men\add* arrived and AvelВҰ153186-Beyt-Maacah. They heaped a siegeВҰ153184 ramp up againstВҰ153191 the cityВҰ153193, and \add also\add* \add вүҲpounded\add* the wallВҰ153205 to \add try to make it\add* \add вүҲcollapse\add*.
\v 16 ThenВҰ153207 a wise womanВҰ153208 calledВҰ153207 out from the cityВҰ153212, вҖңListen, listen, pleaseВҰ153217 tell YoavВҰ153220 to come closer \add вүҲso I can speakВҰ153225 to him\add*.вҖқ
\v 17 \add @Yoav\add* \add вүҲwentВҰ153228 in closer\add* andВҰ153228 \add *she\add* asked, вҖңAre you Yoav?вҖқ
\p вҖңI am,вҖқ he \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\p вҖңListen to \add вүҲwhat your servant has to say\add*,вҖқ she said.
\p вҖңI'm listeningВҰ153242,вҖқ he \add вүҲanswered\add*.
\p
\v 18 ThenВҰ153245 she told him, вҖң\add вүҲLong ago people used to tell others to come here to AvelВҰ153253 to get advice, and they'd do that and thenВҰ153245 be able to settle the matter\add*.
\v 19 I'm a peaceableВҰ153258 and faithfulВҰ153259 \add вүҲcitizen\add* of Yisrael. You're \add вүҲtrying\add* to destroyВҰ153263 \add &this\add* cityВҰ153264 and a motherВҰ153265 inВҰ153266 Yisrael. Why would you \add вүҲwipe out our\add* inheritanceВҰ153269 from YahwehВҰ153270?вҖқ
