\p
\v 1 \add вүҲDuring David'sВҰ153404 reign\add*, there was a three-year famineВҰ153402. David inquired from YahwehВҰ153415 who saidВҰ153417, вҖңSha'ulВҰ153421 \add вүҲand his family have bloodВҰ153425 onВҰ153403 their hands\add*, becauseВҰ153419 he killed the Gibeonites.вҖқ
\v 2 (The Gibeonites were not \add вүҲnative Israelis\add*, but were a remnantВҰ153448 of the AmoritesВҰ153449. The Israelis had \add вүҲpromisedВҰ153452 to protect them\add*, but Sha'ulВҰ153455 had attempted to \add вүҲeliminate\add* them inВҰ153457 his zeal for the peopleВҰ153458 of YisraelВҰ153443 and Yehudah.) \add вүҲSoВҰ153435\add* the kingВҰ153436 summoned the Gibeonites and \add вүҲasked\add* them,\x + \xo 21:2: \xt Josh 9:3-15.\x*
\v 3 вҖңWhat can I do for all of you? How can I \add вүҲremedy\add* \add what was done inВҰ153471 the past\add* so that you all would blessВҰ153473 Yahweh's \add вүҲpeople\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 4 вҖң\add вүҲWe have no claim\add* to goldВҰ153487 or silverВҰ153486 from Sha'ulВҰ153490 or his householdВҰ153493,вҖқ the Gibeonites \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңAnd \add вүҲweВҰ153484 don'tВҰ153482 wish to have anyone\add* inВҰ153499 YisraelВҰ153499 put to deathВҰ153498.вҖқ
\p вҖңThenВҰ153479 what are you sayingВҰ153504 that I can do for you all?вҖқ he \add вүҲasked\add*.
\p
\v 5 вҖңThat manВҰ153512 who \add вүҲcrushed\add* us,вҖқ theyВҰ153508 \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңandВҰ153515 who intended \add вүҲthatВҰ153515 weВҰ153519 be annihilated from within\add* Yisrael'sВҰ153524 borders,
\v 6 give us sevenВҰ153530 \add вүҲof his descendantsВҰ153532\add* and we'll hang them before Yahweh inВҰ153535 GibeahВҰ153535 \add ?вүҲwhere Yahweh's chosenВҰ153537 king Sha'ulВҰ153536 lived\add*.
\p вҖң\add Okay\add*, I'llВҰ153543 give them to you,вҖқ the king \add вүҲrespondedВҰ153540\add*.
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲHowever\add*, the kingВҰ153546 \add вүҲsparedВҰ153545\add* Yonatan's son (and Sha'ul's grandson) Mefiboshet because of the promises thatВҰ153562 he and Yonatan \add вүҲhad made to each other before\add* YahwehВҰ153561.\x + \xo 21:7: \xt 1Sam 20:15-17; 2Sam 9:1-7.\x*
\v 8 \add вүҲInstead\add* \add *he\add* took two of the sons (ArmoniВҰ153587 and Mefiboshet) of Ritsfah (Ayyah's daughter \add вүҲand one of Sha'ul's slave-wives\add*), as well as five sons of Sha'ul's daughter MichalВҰ153595, that she'd bore to AdrielВҰ153601 (the son of BarzillaiВҰ153604, the MeholatiteВҰ153605).\x + \xo 21:8: \xt 1Sam 18:19.\x*
\v 9 He \add вүҲhanded them over to\add* the Gibeonites, and they hung them onВҰ153608 a hillВҰ153611 \add вүҲbefore\add* YahwehВҰ153613, and the seven of them \add вүҲdied\add* togetherВҰ153617. \add вүҲThis happened atВҰ153608\add* the beginning of the barleyВҰ153628 harvest.
\p
\v 10 ThenВҰ153630 Ayyah's daughterВҰ153632 Ritsfah took sackclothВҰ153637 and she spreadВҰ153638 it on the rock \add where the corpses were\add*. She \add вүҲkept the birds away during the\add* day and the animalsВҰ153663 at nightВҰ153665вҖ”\add вүҲstaying there\add* from the beginning of the harvestВҰ153644 untilВҰ153645 \add вүҲthe beginning of the rainy season\add*.
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲDavidВҰ153668 was told\add* what Ritsfah had done,
\v 12 and \add *he\add* wentВҰ153680 and got the bones of Sha'ul and his son Yonatan from the \add вүҲleaders\add* of YabeshВҰ153695-Gilead, who had stolenВҰ153697 them from the squareВҰ153699 of Beyt-Shan whereВҰ153703 the Philistines had hung them thereВҰ153707 onВҰ153715 the dayВҰ153709 the Philistines had \add вүҲdefeated\add* Sha'ul atВҰ153715 GilboaВҰ153715.\x + \xo 21:12: \xt 1Sam 31:8-13.\x*
\v 13 \add @David\add* took Sha'ulВҰ153722 andВҰ153717 Yonatan'sВҰ153726 bones along with the bones of the \add seven\add* \add вүҲmen\add* who'd been hung,
\v 14 andВҰ153734 \add @his men\add* buriedВҰ153734 \add *them\add* in the tombВҰ153746 of Sha'ul's fatherВҰ153748 KishВҰ153747 in Zela (in the Benyamite regionВҰ153743), doing everything that the kingВҰ153754 had commandedВҰ153753. After that, GodВҰ153756 \add вүҲanswered their prayers\add* for the \add вүҲcountry\add*.
