\p
\v 8 These are the namesВҰ154532 of David'sВҰ154535 \add top\add* warriors:
\p \bd Yoshev-Bashshevet\bd* the TahkemoniteВҰ154538 was the head of вҖҳThe ThreeвҖҷ. One timeВҰ154551 he attacked and killed eightВҰ154548 hundredВҰ154549 men withВҰ154551 his spearВҰ154544.
\p
\v 9 Next afterВҰ154556 him was \bd EleazarВҰ154558\bd*, the son of Ahohi's son DodoВҰ154561. \add Once he was\add* amongВҰ154566 the threeВҰ154566 powerful warriors withВҰ154566 DavidВҰ154571 when they taunted the PhilistinesВҰ154573 who were gatheredВҰ154574 thereВҰ154576 for battleВҰ154577. The IsraeliВҰ154579 warriors \add вүҲretreated back up\add* their hill,
\v 10 \add butВҰ154584\add* \add @Eleazar\add* \add вүҲmoved forward and attacked the PhilistinesВҰ154585 untilВҰ154586 his arm became weak, and his hand cramped around\add* his sword. YahwehВҰ154598 \add вүҲachieved\add* a greatВҰ154600 victoryВҰ154599 that dayВҰ154601, and the \add вүҲother warriors\add* only returnedВҰ154604 afterwardsВҰ154605 to plunder \add the dead\add*.
\p
\v 11 Then there was Agge's son \bd ShammaВҰ154612\bd*, the HarariteВҰ154616. The Philistines had assembledВҰ154617 in formationВҰ154619 where there happened to be a fieldВҰ154624 full of lentilsВҰ154626. The \add вүҲIsraelis\add* fled from the Philistines
\v 12 \add вүҲbutВҰ154632\add* \add @Shamma\add* remained there in the middleВҰ154633 of the field and killedВҰ154637 \add many\add* PhilistinesВҰ154640. \add вүҲSoВҰ154632 the field was saved\add*, and YahwehВҰ154642 \add вүҲachieved\add* a greatВҰ154644 victoryВҰ154643.
\p
\v 13 \add Once\add* as it was approaching harvestВҰ154655 time, threeВҰ154648 of вҖҳThe ThirtyвҖҷ wentВҰ154647 to where DavidВҰ154658 \add had been staying\add* atВҰ154666 Adullam'sВҰ154662 cave. There was a Philistine unit camped inВҰ154666 the RefaimВҰ154667 valleyВҰ154666.
\v 14 At the time, DavidВҰ154669 was in the fortress, andВҰ154672 there was \add another\add* Philistine unit in Beyt-Lehem.
\v 15 DavidВҰ154679 \add вүҲwas thirsty\add* \add one day\add* andВҰ154680 \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖңWho'll \add вүҲget me a drinkВҰ154682 of waterВҰ154683\add* from the Beyt-Lehem well by the gateВҰ154689?вҖқ
\v 16 \add вүҲSoВҰ154691\add* the threeВҰ154692 powerfulВҰ154693 warriors \add вүҲbrokeВҰ154691 throughВҰ154691\add* the Philistine campВҰ154694 andВҰ154691 got waterВҰ154698 from the Beyt-Lehem well near the gateВҰ154704. They carriedВҰ154705 it back to DavidВҰ154709, butВҰ154691 he wouldn't drinkВҰ154712 itвҖ”pouring it out instead \add as an offering\add* to YahwehВҰ154715,
\v 17 saying, вҖңFar be it for me, YahwehВҰ154720, \add вүҲto drink\add* thisвҖ”the bloodВҰ154723 of the menВҰ154724 who \add вүҲrisked\add* theirВҰ154726 livesВҰ154726.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ154717\add* he wasn't willingВҰ154728 to drink it.
\p Those \add were some of the\add* things done by вҖҳThe ThreeвҖҷ powerfulВҰ154733 warriorsВҰ154724.
\rem /s1 David's Thirty Mighty Men
\p
\v 18 Yoav's brotherВҰ154737 \bd AbishaiВҰ154736\bd* (Tseruyah's sons) was the head over вҖҳThe ThreeвҖҷ. \add Once\add* he was \add вүҲused\add* his spearВҰ154751 to kill three hundredВҰ154755 \add >fighters\add*, \add вүҲso he was more famous\add* than вҖҳThe ThreeвҖҷ.
\v 19 He was more honouredВҰ154766 than вҖҳThe ThreeвҖҷ and became their leader \add вүҲeven though he wasn't one of\add* вҖҳThe ThreeвҖҷ.
\p
\v 20 Yehoyada's son \bd BenayahВҰ154778\bd* from Kavtsael was a manВҰ154784 of military prowess with many deedsВҰ154790 \add to his name\add*. \add Once\add* he killed вҖҳThe TwoвҖҷ from MoabВҰ154797, and \add another time\add* he wentВҰ154799 down in a pit on a snowyВҰ154808 dayВҰ154807 and killed the lionВҰ154803 in the pit.
\v 21 He \add also\add* killed an impressive Egyptian warrior with a spear, even though Benayah \add вүҲonly held\add* a staff. \add вүҲFirst\add* he snatchedВҰ154826 the spear from the Egyptian's hand, thenВҰ154810 he killed him with his \add own\add* spear.
\v 22 Those \add were some of the\add* things that BenayahВҰ154837 did. He \add вүҲbecame famous\add* alongside вҖҳThe ThreeвҖҷ.
\v 23 (He was more honouredВҰ154850 than вҖҳThe ThirtyвҖҷ butВҰ154851 never entered вҖҳThe ThreeвҖҷ.) DavidВҰ154858 appointedВҰ154857 himВҰ154857 over his bodyguardВҰ154861.
\p
\v 24 \add The following\add* were amongВҰ154870 вҖҳThe ThirtyвҖҷ:
\li1 Yoav's \add other\add* brotherВҰ154867 Asah-ElВҰ154864,
