\p \add There were\add* thirty-seven \add of them\add* \add вүҲin totalВҰ155005\add*.
\c 24
\s1 David takes a census
\rem /s1 David's Census of Israel and Judah; David Counts the Fighting Men; David Takes a Census; David's census
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (1 Chr. 21:1-27)
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ155013 \add вүҲwas angry\add* against Yisrael again and he incitedВҰ155016 DavidВҰ155019 \add вүҲto cause problems for\add* them by saying, вҖңGo \add and\add* \add вүҲorder a census of\add* Yisrael and YehudahВҰ155029.вҖқ
\v 2 \add вүҲSoВҰ155031\add* the kingВҰ155032 told YoavВҰ155035, the commanderВҰ155037 of his army, who was with him \add at the time\add*, вҖң\add вүҲTravel throughout\add* all the \add regions of\add* the IsraeliВҰ155048 tribesВҰ155048, from DanВҰ155050 \add (in the far north)\add* down to BeerВҰ155053-Sheva \add (in the far south)\add*, andВҰ155031 count the people so that I'llВҰ155059 know the numberВҰ155061 of \add вүҲfighting men\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 вҖңMayВҰ155071 your godВҰ155072 YahwehВҰ155082 multiply the peopleВҰ155075 a hundredВҰ155079 timesВҰ155080 \add over\add*,вҖқ YoavВҰ155066 respondedВҰ155065, вҖңadd may my master the king \add вүҲsee that happen, butВҰ155065\add* why would my master the king \add вүҲwant to do that\add*?вҖқ
\v 4 \add вүҲHowever,\add* the king \add вүҲinsisted, so even though\add* YoavВҰ155099 andВҰ155093 the army commanders \add disagreed\add*, \add вүҲat the king's command\add* \add *they\add* \add вүҲset off to count\add* the Israeli peopleВҰ155112.
\p
\v 5 They crossedВҰ155117 the YordanВҰ155120 \add river\add* andВҰ155117 campedВҰ155121 in AroerВҰ155122, southВҰ155123 of the cityВҰ155124 in the middleВҰ155126 of the GadВҰ155129 valleyВҰ155128, thenВҰ155117 \add proceeded\add* to YazerВҰ155132.
\v 6 ThenВҰ155134 they wentВҰ155134 \add north\add* to GileadВҰ155135 and the land of TahtimВҰ155140-Hodshi, \add before\add* coming to DanВҰ155142-Yaan and aroundВҰ155144 to Tsidon.
\v 7 ThenВҰ155149 they cameВҰ155149 to the Tsor \add (TyreВҰ155153)\add* fortressВҰ155151 and all the citiesВҰ155156 of the HivitesВҰ155157 and the CanaanitesВҰ155158 \add вүҲbefore going\add* \add east\add* to Be'er-Sheva in the NegevВҰ155162 \add wilderness\add* (part of YehudahВҰ155163).
\v 8 \add вүҲSoВҰ155167 theyВҰ155171 travelled throughout the land for\add* nineВҰ155173 monthsВҰ155174 andВҰ155167 twentyВҰ155175 days \add вүҲbefore returning\add* to YerushalemВҰ155177.
\v 9 ThenВҰ155179 YoavВҰ155180 \add вүҲreported the census results\add* to the kingВҰ155189: 800,000 fighting swordsmenВҰ155199 in YisraelВҰ155191, andВҰ155179 500,000 in YehudahВҰ155201.
\rem /s1 Judgment for David's Sin; Judgment on David's Sin
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲHowever, DavidВҰ155211 had a guilty conscience\add* afterВҰ155213 he'd had the peopleВҰ155219 countedВҰ155216 andВҰ155208 he told Yahweh, вҖңI've \add вүҲdisobeyed you badly, butВҰ155208\add* now, Yahweh, pleaseВҰ155234 \add вүҲtakeВҰ155232 away\add* the iniquityВҰ155237 of your servantВҰ155238 because I've been very foolishВҰ155240.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 \add WhenВҰ155256\add* DavidВҰ155244 got up inВҰ155245 the morningВҰ155245, YahwehВҰ155249 \add вүҲgave\add* the prophetВҰ155254 GadВҰ155253 \add this\add* messageВҰ155247
\v 12 to take to DavidВҰ155263, вҖңI, YahwehВҰ155266, am \add вүҲoffering you threeВҰ155267 choices\add*. \add вүҲYou decide which one I should carry out against\add* you.вҖқ
\v 13 ThenВҰ155281 GadВҰ155283 \add вүҲasked\add* \add *him\add*, вҖң\add вүҲDo you want\add* sevenВҰ155294 yearsВҰ155295 of famineВҰ155297 in your country, or three monthsВҰ155303 of fleeingВҰ155304 from your enemies, or three daysВҰ155315 of plague in your country? \add вүҲConsider those andВҰ155281 let me knowВҰ155319 which option to pass back\add* to the one who sentВҰ155324 me.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 DavidВҰ155329 \add вүҲanswered\add* GadВҰ155332, вҖң\add вүҲThis is very distressingВҰ155333\add*, \add butВҰ155328\add* pleaseВҰ155339 \add вүҲlet YahwehВҰ155342 be the one to punish me because he's very mercifulвҖ”don'tВҰ155351 let other men be the ones\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 \add вүҲSoВҰ155355\add* YahwehВҰ155356 \add вүҲsent\add* a plague to YisraelВҰ155358 from the morningВҰ155359 andВҰ155355 until the time \add вүҲhe'd decided\add*. Seventy thousandВҰ155374 peopleВҰ155367 died from DanВҰ155368 \add in the north\add* \add вүҲdown\add* to BeerВҰ155371-Sheva \add in the south\add*.
\v 16 \add вүҲWhen\add* \add Yahweh's\add* messenger stretchedВҰ155377 out his hand to destroy YerushalemВҰ155381 \add withВҰ155391 the plague\add*, Yahweh relented concerningВҰ155385 the disaster andВҰ155377 told the messenger who was \add вүҲdestroying\add* many peopleВҰ155391, вҖңNow lower your hand.вҖқ \add When he said that,\add* \add *his\add* messenger was near the threshingВҰ155401 floorВҰ155401 of Aravnah the YebusiteВҰ155404.
\p
\v 17 DavidВҰ155408 \add вүҲhad complained\add* to YahwehВҰ155411 when he saw the messengerВҰ155416 \add вүҲafflicting\add* the people, \add вүҲsaying\add*, вҖңListen, \add вүҲit's me alone who\add* sinnedВҰ155423, and I myself \add вүҲwho disobeyed you\add*. \add вүҲButВҰ155407\add* theseВҰ155426 \add innocent\add* \add вүҲpeople\add*вҖ”what have they done? Please, \add вүҲjust punish only me and my relatives\add*.вҖқ
\s2 David builds an altar
\rem /s1 David's Altar on the Threshing Floor; David Builds an Altar
\p
\v 18 GadВҰ155440 cameВҰ155438 to DavidВҰ155443 that dayВҰ155444, and \add вүҲinstructed\add* him, вҖңGo to the YebusiteВҰ155455 Aravnah's threshingВҰ155452 floorВҰ155452 \add and\add* \add вүҲbuild\add* an altarВҰ155451 to YahwehВҰ155450 \add there\add*.вҖқ
\v 19 \add вүҲSoВҰ155457\add* DavidВҰ155458 went \add вүҲthere just as YahwehВҰ155464 had instructedВҰ155463 him through Gad'sВҰ155461 messageВҰ155459\add*.
\v 20 \add вүҲWhenВҰ155466\add* Aravnah lookedВҰ155466 \add вүҲout\add* and saw the king and his servantsВҰ155474 \add вүҲapproaching\add*, \add *he\add* went out and \add вүҲfell to his knees in frontВҰ155481 of the king and bowedВҰ155479 his faceВҰ155481\add* to the groundВҰ155482.
\v 21 вҖңWhy would my masterВҰ155488 the kingВҰ155490 comeВҰ155487 to his servantВҰ155493?вҖқ Aravnah asked.
\p вҖң\add вүҲI want to buy your\add* threshingВҰ155500 floorВҰ155500 to buildВҰ155501 an altarВҰ155502 for YahwehВҰ155488,вҖқ DavidВҰ155495 \add вүҲanswered\add*. вҖң\add вүҲSoВҰ155484\add* that the plagueВҰ155505 \add вүҲafflicting\add* the peopleВҰ155507 \add вүҲcan be stopped\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 22 вҖңMay my masterВҰ155516 the kingВҰ155517 takeВҰ155514 \add it\add*,вҖқ Aravnah respondedВҰ155509. вҖң\add вүҲUse it inВҰ155519 whatever way you think best\add*. See, \add you can use\add* the oxen for the burntВҰ155523 offeringВҰ155515, and the threshingВҰ155524 instruments and the oxen's equipmentВҰ155525 for firewood.
\v 23 \add *I\add* give \add it all\add* to \add you\add*, the king. May your godВҰ155541 YahwehВҰ155540 acceptВҰ155542 your \add offering\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 24 вҖңNo,вҖқ the kingВҰ155545 \add вүҲanswered\add*. вҖңI'llВҰ155554 definitely \add вүҲbuy\add* it from youВҰ155555. I couldn't \add вүҲofferВҰ155558 something to\add* my godВҰ155560 YahwehВҰ155559 \add that cost me\add* nothing.вҖқ
\v 25 \add вүҲSoВҰ155575\add* DavidВҰ155577 builtВҰ155575 an altarВҰ155578 thereВҰ155576 to Yahweh, and he \add вүҲinstructed for\add* burntВҰ155581 offerings and peaceВҰ155582 offerings to \add вүҲbe made\add*. ThenВҰ155575 Yahweh \add вүҲaccepted prayers for the country\add* and the plagueВҰ155587 against YisraelВҰ155589 was \add вүҲstopped\add*.
